text: happy birthday to one of the most inspiring women of all time!!! @therealmariskahargitay you have touched my life in amazing ways. so wild how the universe works in timing! after going through a horrific long term relationship i had fallen into a deep depression & began to isolate myself. i began watching @nbcsvu all day, everyday... one day i came across @thejhf, which i later found out you created based off of the letters you were receiving when you started the show. after some things processed in my mind through speaking with people in your foundation, i chose to tell my story. after 4 years of silence & pain, i finally got to tell my story! this opened an entire new chapter of my life & man i must say i am so thankful 🥰 you have not only touched my life... but you changed it forever . i am forever grateful & although you may never personally see this, i just need to wish you a very happy birthday. you’ve done absolutely amazing things. because of you... i am no longer a victim, but a survivor 💪🏽 #thankyou #sexualassault #domesticviolence #childsabuse #metoo #tellyourstory #better #strongwomen #stronger #fightyourfight #loveyourself #nosecrets #noregrets #strength #motivation #inspiration #change #changeyourlife #incontrol #myinspiration #mariskahargitay #mariska #joyful #joyfulheart #joyfulheartfoundation #peace #love #pixiedust

text:
the evolutionary imperative, rendered compulsory thanks to our cosmic cohorts and unmissable by eclipsia, is bolstered today by the sun crossing paths with lilith in aquaria.

black moon lilith is a chart position that screams directly to our wounded feminine and how she transmutes her rage into power. in aquaria, lilith is the rebellious enchantrix who tolerates nothing less than her true worth. she is an electrical storm of the highest frequency, cultivating alternative paths to her humanitarian goals and sweeping everything along in her thrall.

violence against women - physically / emotionally / psychologically / economically / socially / hierarchically - continues unabated. meanwhile men meltdown over razor ads and bully anyone who calls them on it, a privileged irony bomb if ever there was one. just like lilith, women are no longer prepared to take this lying down. #metoo got everyone on the battlefield but war is never the answer. it is now beyond time for innovative approaches that engender real change and genuine equality.

the feminine is justifiably enraged, an anger that can be channelled constructively or destructively. anger is an ally that can galvanise right action, heart centered and fair. the changes required - and thus their ripple through our worlds - begin at home, like all the best virtues do. it is time to call out violence against women in all its myriad insidious forms. in our families. in our relationships. in our communities.

lilith is throwing her catalytic weight around in aquaria until may. she asks us each and all to channel her creativity and vision into what really makes our blood boil, in order to effect lasting change. she opens your eyes, points your finger and raises your voice against injustice. she is fearless, driven and will march upon the gated palace if she cannot see its columns crumbling any other way.

your anger and your dissatisfaction has a purpose.
use it for its highest good.

image one of @sarahmgellar - her lilith in aquaria - via @emotionalclub | image two of yours truly banging on about this in circle - my lilith also in aquaria - overlaid with the blazing words of @nikita_gill

violence against women - physically / emotionally / psychologically / economically / socially / hierarchically - continues unabated. meanwhile men meltdown over razor ads and bully anyone who calls them on it, a privileged irony bomb if ever there was one. just like lilith, women are no longer prepared to take this lying down.  got everyone on the battlefield but war is never the answer. it is now beyond time for innovative approaches that engender real change and genuine equality.

the feminine is justifiably enraged, an anger that can be channelled constructively or destructively. anger is an ally that can galvanise right action, hea centered and fair. the changes required - and thus their ripple through our worlds - begin at home, like all the best viues do. it is time to call out violence against women in all its myriad insidious forms. in our families. in our relationships. in our communities.

lilith is throwing her catalytic weight around in aquaria until may. she asks us each and all to channel her creativity and vision into what really makes our blood boil, in order to effect lasting change. she opens your eyes, points your finger and raises your voice against injustice. she is fearless, driven and will march upon the gated palace if she cannot see its columns crumbling any other way.

your anger and your dissatisfaction has a purpose.
use it for its highest good.

repost part2🔥🔥: so, the host of the night club in atlanta #atlopera #operanightclub made a post a few days ago. wasnt able to get it to work until now. 👍🏽 repost: it literally broke my heart to see the videos of this young woman #jasmineeiland being taken advantage of in an establishment while i was hosting!! i move through my city alone often, so this hit really close to home. i’m terrified. if anyone knows jasmine, let her know i’m here if she needs anything! no woman should be taken advantage of regardless of what she’s wearing, how drunk she is, how she’s dancing! stop with the excuses!! we have to fight for our sisters!! and to all my peers in the club industry we need to come together to figure out how can we better protect our women! we need to open our dialogue, we need to be proactive! if i’m afraid, i know there are so many other women that are! if you don’t address it now, it could drastically effect your event outcomes and even the liquor sales bc at this point is not accepting a drink from anyone! so to my brothers, promoters and owners let’s step up and do our part, how can we create a safe environment for our women to come out and enjoy themselves???ldfuriousent @agentertainmentdolodorsey @chrisstainles_susolo @botchey@kbotchey@djholida @jabbarcas
#jasmineeiland #womensrights #protectourwomen #justiceforjasmine

text:
в скандинавской культуре есть такие люди - скальды - поэты-писатели-музыканты, в общем умные и креативные специалисты медиапространства, только много сотен и тыщ лет назад. по легендам (по некоторым, а их много) они появились в следствие того, что один, который бог, мчась на своём коне по небу разлил из своей чаши какой-то убермёд, испив который люди стали скальдами. а потом один, кхм-кхм, испорожнился этим мёдом, и те, кто это самое испили, стали плохими скальдами, у которых напрочь отсутствовали способности к ясному изложению мысли, и, что самое главное, эта самая мысль (то есть сознание, как я это понял) в них тоже отсутствовала. так вот, сдаётся мне, что все обитатели социальных сетей, которые что-то пытаются писать, это потомки вторых, что возомнили себя первыми. 
зато некоторые, в том числе и я, лечат здесь приступы графоманства. 5 лет я делал это анонимно и в тех местах, где никто из моих подписчиков не сидит. ну что ж. пришло время и мне сделать каминг аут: я - графоман. сделай и ты, это как #metoo, только здорового человека

text: one year ago today i was raped on a tinder date and sent home bleeding and covered in bruises, scabies, and strangulation marks. my rapist is a regular performer at uptown arts bar. a few months after he raped me, he posted a youtube video of himself onstage at uptown arts bar performing a poem called “fuck me” that he had previously told me was about the night of our tinder date. in the video he’s met by an ocean of applause from a crowd who doesn’t know that they’ve just heard a poem about a night of what was actually violent date rape and not the “great session of recovery sex” that he so lovingly describes in his poem. having been to poetry night at uptown arts bar before, i knew that it was considered to be the most “safe” and “feminist” bar in kc and that a large chunk of the women who i’d seen perform poetry there were rape survivors, many of whom i’d seen perform slam poems about men who had raped them on the same stage that my own rapist was now taking. assuming that there was no way that this kind of thing would fly with the self-proclaimed ardent “feminists” who ran the bar, i went to the bar and told them what had happened. they had the person in charge of the poetry night contact me, and after having multiple conversations with both her and the manager of the bar, they told me that they had decided to permanently ban my rapist from the bar. two weeks later, the person who runs the poetry night texted me notifying me that the bar had changed their minds and that the ban would be lifted after one month, at which point my rapist could continue to perform there regularly. when i asked for an explanation as to why they had gone back on the permanent ban, i was given no such explanation and both she and the manager of the bar asked me to leave them alone. i’ve spent the last year not knowing what to do with this information. today i’m saying something. finally. please tell your friends that uptown arts bar is not, in fact, the “safe” or “feminist” space that it claims to be and that the management is knowingly letting my rapist share not only this bar with rape victims, but also their stage, their platform, their applause, and their “safety.”

text:
menstrual equity *is* equality! that’s why we’re calling on city councils, school boards, and public schools across the country to provide free and accessible period products for all of their students. learn more about our campaign and join the movement at shethinx.com/me . over the last few months, 11 of our @periodmovement chapters have been hard at work mobilizing to push forward #periodpolicy to end period poverty in schools in their local communities. it’s been absolutely inspiring to see how much progress has already been made, and how much more people are talking about the #menstrualmovement as a result of their work. fight on! 👊🏽❤️
.
excited to be one of the menstrual heroines for this campaign along with @jenniferweisswolf @girlsinc - co-created between @periodmovement and @shethinx #unitedforaccess. stay tuned because we have something big planned for this coming monday, can’t wait for the world to see. 🙈

text:
femmsouth has officially launched!! in our first podcast episode, amaya and i discuss what it’s like being a feminist living in the deep south.  we discuss the challenges of being raised in the south, of having to really leave the south and go to college to learn about feminism.  we talk about our calling to bring awareness to women that have not had access to feminist theory and history or that fear speaking out because of the dominant culture here.  we hope you join our conversation.  please subscribe to our femmsouth podcast on itunes, soundcloud, spotify, and let us know what you think.  visit our website, femmsouth.com, and subscribe to receive our newsletter.  we will give you updates on our new episodes, book reviews, and blog posts.

text: your reminder of who’s to blame for shutting down our government. it’s all about you donald #trump! you offered to “take the mantle” on december 11, 2018 — it’s all about you — and only you! day 33…you now are responsible for the longest shutdown in u.s. history. you blew away the [one and only] shutdown under #obama and surpassed the record for longest government shutdown — topping the 21 day shutdown under bill clinton. 800,000+ federal workers are now going without multiple paychecks [including some legally required to still work] and countless other americans are feeling the residual effects of this painful and dumb #trumpshutdown. out of touch and just plain cruel. reopen the government now! but, why exactly is our government shutdown over american taxpayers paying for the wall — when #mexico is supposed to be paying for the wall? i don't give a crap about his fan’s spins and interpretations of what he meant to say, or what he really means… he said: "i will build a great wall -- and nobody builds walls better than me, believe me --and i'll build them very inexpensively. i will build a great, great wall on our southern border, and i will make mexico pay for that wall. mark my words." words…marked. he was very clear and specific. he even put it in writing! he wants money for his stupid wall?…it's going to have to be in pesos. end of discussion. #democrats now control of the house and will put forth sensible legislation to benefit the people of this country. and, for the first time, will conduct real congressional oversight of #trump…his life will now [and deservedly so] become a virtual and perpetual deep colonoscopy…the saudis. abuse of power. corruption. ethics. kavanaugh. tax returns. obstruction of justice. #russia….you name it…we'll really start getting to the bottom of it…all! to save #america we must hold to account the inept, corrupt and amoral unindicted co-conspirator in the oval office: #illegitimate #failingpresident #donaldtrump. #washingtondc #lovetrumpshate #nevertrump #msnbc #foxnews #cnn #journalism #moveon #trumpprotest #notmypresident #politics #journalism #indivisible #makeamericagreatagain #womensmarch #crazytown #metoo #bluewave #maga

text:
many people have asked me what have i seen as the biggest improvement in my life since i started removing toxic chemicals out of our home.  the answer is simple...my hormones, by far have been the greatest improvement for me physically.  william can attest to the fact that i was a hot mess all the time, so up and down.  it wasn't fun for me or him or anyone that came in contact with me. 
toxic chemicals cause harm to our bodies and they are hormone disrupters.  it’s no wonder i was always having a hard time.  i had air fresheners in every room of our house and i had candles lit all the time, not to mention that i am a neat freak and cleaned with bleach 3 times a week.  so once i started eliminating the chemicals and replacing them with plant based products and quality essential oils, it was as if i had finally balanced out.  i am now being supported hormonally instead of disrupted. 
i make my own perfumes now using oils and i clean with an all purpose cleaner that boosts my immune system. these do not disrupt my hormones. 
comment below with 🙋🏻‍♀️ for a free sample of my plant based cleaner. also check out my igtv video for what else  i use for hormone support. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
#holisticliving #wellness #wellnessinsideout #agouldstory #fgnaturalwellness #selfcare #wellnesswednesday #metoo #healthyliving #healthyhome #healthyfamilies #plantbasedlifestyle

it’s not easy trying to heal from past abuse when the people that should be understanding, condemn you for not handling it the way they want you to. it’s sad how people try to manipulate survivors and victims to make them feel guilty for being hurt by what happened to them. they accuse the person of not letting go, accuse them of being selfish, make them seem petty, trying to make themself feel better for never helping or protecting or taking action when the abuse came to light. well i’m here to say that no one should minimize another person’s experience, tell them how to deal with it and make them feel bad for speaking up about how they were wronged. thank you for coming to my rant, have a nice night.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
when i went to bed yesterday my girl beside me had played with my phone, and left this picture. i look into her eyes and wish her the best inspiring happy life she can imagine. always follow your heart! but it also reminded me travelling back from thailand yesterday. sitting in the senator lounge at frankfurt i looked around among the business people. i was off course the only one in big yoga pants and a soft sweater. but my chlothing was not the main reason why i where different from the others in the lounge. do you know what it was? i was female. and yes i was in a business lounge in not dubai or doha it was frankfurt!!! there was not 70, 80, 90 percent of men, it was 99 percent😳why? do women not use business class, do they not work abroad, are they choosing not to travel? will they rather be home with their families? i actually do not have the answer. do you know? @katarinawennstam @the_future_is_equal @gretathunberg 
it is 2019 and this strange dispersion does not reflect the everyday work as i do in engineering and new technology. .
.
.

text: harvey weinstein. les moonves. getting called out by people who were bullied, harassed, and abused. the draw of entertainment requires similar traits of the people who were called by fashion. passion, creativity, vision, talent, imagination, hardcore will, grit, relentless work ethic, willingness to understand that there is grime behind the glamour - and nerves of steel. so how much is too much?  people have come forward in tech and entertainment, and why not fashion yet? it isn’t a question of is this happening? the question is, why haven’t people come forward yet? the majority of employees in fashion are women. the majority of ceo’s are not. but the problem is far greater than simply gender, while male patriarchy plays an more complicated and powerful force in retail and fashion. from a higher perspective, retail is a sector where the path is often unclear, the rules unwritten, and the pathways obstructed by invisible understandings - and lets not forget the powerless hr department. a cultural truth of traditional retail that it is slow to change with the times, an example of that is its comedically slow adoption of tech, terrible online shopping experiences and now playing an awkward game of catching up. while there may be a lack of willingness to listen from the top of the triangle 👁 and a fostered culture of passive acceptance and silenced hierarchy below, and the fundamental truth is coming. it wasn’t cool to cause a stir. it wasn’t cool to be the “activist” non-shit taker in the past. but intolerance is now. @wwd @refinery29 @nytimesfashion @vice we’re talking to you, too - we need your help in highlighting these issues. to all the people at the top who know you’re doing something so, so wrong - see you in a netflix series in 2020. props to @viktorandrolf for setting the 2019 mood and @bof for being the fresh source of fashion reporting we all deserve. 💯 #retailslambook #retailstrategy #metoo #retailbusiness #retailfails #empowerment #nah #viktorandrolf #retailradicals #retailproblems #businessoffashion #wwd #fashionista #racked #fyrefestival #fyre #corporateretail #hereforit

text:
❄⛄в саратове опять снег!!!! ❄❄❄и опять каакой🤦🏻‍♂!!!!!!!
притча по поводу:
в одной местности долго не было дождя... люди боялись, что посевы пропадут, будет голод... ни молитвы, ни жертвоприношения, ни стрельба по облакам не помогали... наместник решился на последнюю меру и пригласил странствующего монаха-даоса. приехав, тот заперся в пустой хижине на окраине. он сидел там пару дней и... наконец пошёл долгожданный дождь. жители восприняли это как должное: пришёл даос и всё исправил. но наместник несмотря ни на что был удивлен... он спросил даоса: – как тебе удалось вызвать дождь? – какой дождь? я не вызывал никакого дождя – удивился даос; – когда я только приехал, я увидел, что здесь нарушено дао, и от этого нарушается моё собственное дао. тогда я заперся в хижине и восстанавливал своё дао; теперь оно восстановлено, и я ухожу... ❄❄❄❄❄❄
в саратове, кажется слишком много даосов 🤣 господа просветленные, астанавитесь! ⛔ лучше начните решать проблему с помощью #visiotuning ! ⚠ пишите запрос в личном сообщении в direct, чтобы заказать консультацию! всё проще, чем кажется!

text:
we marched for our survivors & for those who are victims. 
we marched for justice & equal rights. 
we marched for our mothers, our aunts, our nieces, our sisters and our daughters.
we marched for each other.
we marched as one. ✊🏼
.
.
.
2 years ago i would have never step foot in the city that haunts me the most. #riverside is where i was assaulted. exactly a mile in a half from this very location. i showed up that morning to face my fears & i was fortunate enough to do it with my biggest supporters! 🥰
.
.
.
the women you see beside me are very important. 
the blonde is my #advocate tammy (@advocategirl1)
who answered the 3am phone call 2 years ago from the crisis hotline.
stating that a victim was in need & was being rushed to the er. that victim was me. .
.
.
tammy, is my guardian angel.
i cannot wait for you all to meet her .
.
.
the brunette in the grey, is someone i met last year in #supportgroup. with our assaults only being 2weeks apart there is a deep bond we share together. from healing together & now #activists together.
meet isabel, one bad ass chick who continues to amaze me. she is so strong & someone i have grown very close to. isabel will be hosting a #selflove workshop next month in riverside & i have been offered to be 1 of her guest speakers 🙏🏽 ♥️
.
.
.
.
beside her is two remarkable women who have served their time educating,volunteering, and loving on survivors of assault @rarcc_support .
countless hours fueled with passion for change! .
.
.
.
these are the women who made this #womensmarch2019  possible for me to do.😭
_
_
_
without them, i would have not shown. but because of them & their support for the past 2 years..... i am alive &
i am hear to make an
i m p a c t 📢✨
.
.
.

tweet_full:
we marched for our survivors & for those who are victims. 
we marched for justice & equal rights. 
we marched for our mothers, our aunts, our nieces, our sisters and our daughters.
we marched for each other.
we marched as one. ✊🏼
.
.
.
2 years ago i would have never step foot in the city that haunts me the most. #riverside is where i was assaulted. exactly a mile in a half from this very location. i showed up that morning to face my fears & i was fortunate enough to do it with my biggest supporters! 🥰
.
.
.
the women you see beside me are very important. 
the blonde is my #advocate tammy (@advocategirl1)
who answered the 3am phone call 2 years ago from the crisis hotline.
stating that a victim was in need & was being rushed to the er. that victim was me. .
.
.
tammy, is my guardian angel.
i cannot wait for you all to meet her .
.
.
the brunette in the grey, is someone i met last year in #supportgroup. with our assaults only being 2weeks apart there is a deep bond we share together. from healing together & now #activists together.
meet isabel, one bad ass chick who continues to amaze me. she is so strong & someone i have grown very close to. isabel will be hosting a #selflove workshop next month in riverside & i have been offered to be 1 of her guest speakers 🙏🏽 ♥️
.
.
.
.
beside her is two remarkable women who have served their time educating,volunteering, and loving on survivors of assault @rarcc_support .
countless hours fueled with passion for change! .
.
.
.
these are the women who made this #womensmarch2019  possible for me to do.😭

_
without them, i would have not shown. but because of them & their support for the past 2 years..... i am alive &

text:
deux extraits d'un article sur la solitude des personnes trans sur le site the independent.
être trans c'est souvent être seule. seule d'abord quand on comprend qu'on n'est pas ce qu'on pensait être. ce qu'on nous a appris. seule aussi quand on commence à souffrir d'un corps qu'on voit comme une cage. seule aussi face au débat autour de la transition, seule quand il s'agit d'annoncer, de se dévoiler. seule quand il s'agit de se relever d'une agression transphobe. seule quand la dysphorie frappe. seule face aux inconvénients des traitements et chirurgies....
je n'oublie pas le soutien. il existe et est absolument nécessaire.
malheureusement il ne peut pas exister et être là pour tout, certains aspects de la transidentite sont des luttes en solitaires, que nous seules pouvons comprendre vraiment et gérer. la solitude est une composante intrinsèque de la transidentité.
dans la société la bienveillance et le soutien ne sont pas la norme pour nous (pas la norme, la majorité mais il fzut dire que la bienveillance existe quand même aussi, merci à vous tou-s-tes). agressions, viols, insultes, menaces, mépris, manque de visibilité, discrimination à l'embauche, au physique, moqueries... les difficultés sont quotidiennes.
on nous oublie beaucoup. une des preuves récentes de cet oubli de la communauté trans est le mouvement #metoo. cette prise de parole massive des femmes face au sexisme, aux violences qu'elles subissent est absolument nécessaire et beau, et inspirant. à 10000% et ce mouvement doit continuer et fleurir.
mais il doit continuer en nous incluant. jusqu'ici il nous a oublié alors que nous vivons les mêmes choses à cause de notre identité. je n'accuse personne, je n'attaque rien, mais il est nécessaire de souligner les manques pour les corriger. pour inclure plus.

nous aussi nous sommes agressées parce que nous sommes des femmes. trans.

text:
denim-child #jiosaavn
and pack-up! the smiles reserved for post-shoot for my brand new audio show on @jiosaavn because at that shoot i didn’t get to smile at all! however , i can’t wait for us all to be part of that conversation.  inspired by the #metoo movement, which cannot be a fad, a flash in the pan,something that only happens in and on the media or on sm, we bring you #mainbhi. based on true stories of real women it is an attempt to make women and men listening everywhere realise that it is upto each of us  to stand up for ourselves and for each other. that it isn’t a ‘big city, bade log, unki industry’ wala phenomenon but a fight every woman puts up everyday in the streets, office, festivals, parties, buses...and even at home.  a revolution of respect must begin and this is a small step in that direction. this is for the women and for the men who stand by them.  i’m ever thankful that i started the movement on @redfmindia , a place that has always allowed me to be who i am and has always backed things that need to be spoken about and i continue to do so every morning.
a big thanks to the folks at @jiosaavn for helping my voice be the voice of so many women i stand with and whose stories i hear everyday. #mainbhi my new audio show you can find on #jiosaavn. it starts today. let me know what you think. i’m putting it up on all platforms soon. with love #givingback #standingwith aapka saath #mainbhi.

text:
today i got my body scan results, and they practically solidified how much fun i’ve had over the past 6 months 😂 but i’m not mad, how could i be? 
this before picture is me 6kgs above my admittance weight to inpatient. i’m now 16kgs heavier than that :) but i’ve gained so much more. i never thought there would be a time where i could say i’m “recovered” from my eating disorder, but i’m only reminded of my past when i go to the doctors; i’m only reminded when i stumble across old photos; i’m only reminded when people message me for advice. that’s what it is right now, a memory. i eat and drink in abundance (and balance) and with little to no thought. i train with strength and power, i live and laugh and love with all that i am, and i feel alive. 
so that’s why i’m not mad that i’ve gained a little fat or lost a little muscle, because in the past few months i have lived a life 14-18 year old me never thought i’d really be able to; i’ve lived a life eating disorder free, and nothing can take that from me🥰
name: Too Sassy For My Own Good

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

cnn

text:
¿es solo un chiste?

el lenguaje inclusivo, pretende romper con la forma en que lo masculino se ha impuesto como universal. hacer broma de esto, repitiendo lugares comunes, es ignorar la complejidad del debate que existen al interior. es subestimar y rebajar la lucha femenina. revela total desconocimiento sobre el lenguaje inclusivo y la cuestión de género. es un hecho muy desafortunado, sobre todo porque se hace uso de la televisión pública. 
no olvidemos @andreubuenafuente  @silviabril que la televisión, a parte de informar, trasmite conceptos e ideas, en este caso equivocadas, que no hacen más que confundir y denostar.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
but wylie wasn’t just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: “information operations”, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us military’s doctrine of the “five-dimensional battle space”. his brief ranged across the scl group – the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it.
.
- it’s like dirty mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.’
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer – the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates – and his daughter rebekah.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
il y a un an dans courrier. 🗄⏪
“si la question est de savoir si la campagne #metoo est allée trop loin ou pas assez, la réponse est : les deux.” article publié le 24 janvier 2018] les détracteurs du mouvement #metoo oublient que les femmes ont le droit de se battre pour préserver leur liberté. les choses ont changé et la société doit se réinventer, estime cette journaliste américaine dans le guardian. 
c’est en recevant une énième invitation à lire la tribune prodigieusement stupide de catherine deneuve – censée me ravir et me rassurer sur le fait que tout le monde n’avait pas cédé à la folie du mouvement #metoo – que j’ai envisagé de rédiger une réponse automatique à ces messages : “si la question est de savoir si la campagne #metoo est allée trop loin ou pas assez, la réponse est : les deux. choisir un camp contre un autre, c’est faire preuve d’étroitesse de vue politique.” en effet, il me semble que je comprends le point de vue des signataires de ce texte maladroit. je suis néanmoins en profond désaccord avec elles.

elles pointent à juste titre les “excès” de la campagne #metoo, mais elles ne comprennent absolument pas en quoi ce mouvement ne va en même temps pas assez loin. certes, des hommes accusés sans preuve peuvent voir leur carrière injustement brisée et, oui, un certain nombre de récentes accusations relèvent d’anecdotes dont n’importe qui devrait pouvoir se remettre. mais cela ne suffit pas pour nier la portée politique de ce mouvement.

on devine que la résistance au mouvement #metoo ne relève pas seulement d’un sentiment de camaraderie entre hommes se retrouvant sur le banc des accusés. la tentation de réguler certains domaines ou comportements que l’on qualifiera de “limites” – les blagues, les sous-entendus, certains livres ou œuvres d’art – suscite une grande inquiétude.

pour bon nombre de femmes, notamment hétérosexuelles, ces zones grises sont aussi le sel de la vie. flirter est un moyen de se rassurer sur sa capacité à inspirer le désir. un baiser volé ouvre de nouvelles possibilités, c’est quelque chose d’inattendu et de potentiellement excitant. la licence sexuelle des hommes peut être attirante.
name: feminin in society

on devine que la résistance au mouvement #metoo ne relève pas seulement d’un sentiment de camaraderie entre hommes se retrouvant sur le banc des accusés. la tentation de réguler certains domaines ou comportements que l’on qualifiera de “limites” – les blagues, les sous-entendus, certains livres ou œuvres d’art – suscite une grande inquiétude.

pour bon nombre de femmes, notamment hétérosexuelles, ces zones grises sont aussi le sel de la vie. flirter est un moyen de se rassurer sur sa capacité à inspirer le désir. un baiser volé ouvre de nouvelles possibilités, c’est quelque chose d’inattendu et de potentiellement excitant. la licence sexuelle des hommes peut être attirante.

text: i know people will have their opinions.... im not asking for them so please dont share. im not attacking, insulting or intending to offend. its because i love everyone and understand that the journey in life can seem difficult is why i share this. im not saying its an easy journey to evolved through..however in the end its worth it. all roads are not easy in life. however, if you're seeking the truth for life not primarily self but life itself..in the end the answer that you shall find will be liberating. aspire to love on a spiritual love before you focus on trying to express it..try understanding what love is supposed to do to your life, my beloved fellow humans who are also part of lgbtq community.matthew 7:1-3.*god alone can judge you all* i've been down this road before.. im not going to say its going to be easy no longer living this way however, when you truly experience the love of our creator..it gives you strength to get through each day while building your love and reverence for the most high..its not about what you lustfully desire but what life truly desires for you. grow from the journey dont just stay there in the same spot. #love #loveiskey #joy #peace #smiles #laughter # us #metoo #blacklivesmatter #freedom #lgbtq #live #in #truth #not #lies #running #scream #rooftop #hispanic #black #allraces #blessed #favoured

this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
it took me 10 years to get ahold of this letter. a letter my rapist sent me from prison. i still to this day have no idea how this made it out of burnside. there was a no contact order, the guards are suppose to read mail, and i dont know how he got my address. i went through a horrible trial for him to be found guilty, and he received 2 years and 6 months with time served. so in reality he got 6 months by the time sentencing came around. 
#metoo

dudes
dudes, what’s with all the
bitches ‘n’ hoes?
suck this & take thot
drip drop sizzle splot
dudes, what’s with all the not
listening to no’s!
from just plain old disrespect
to straight old rrrrrape
no. means. no.

dudes, go slow
play nice
what you don’t know
it’s what it’s worth
to do things from a place of trust
it’s nice to be nice
and nicer to play nicely
so for the sake of women 
everywhere, listen to me

to straight old rrrrrape
no. means. no.

play nice
what you don’t know
it’s what it’s worth
to do things from a place of trust
it’s nice to be nice
and nicer to play nicely
so for the sake of women 
everywhere, listen to me

text: sund arbejdskultur er vigtigt for filmværkstedet/københavn, og vi lægger derfor op til at følge de anbefalinger som står i rapporten “from #metoo til we do” (👉🏼filmworkshop.dk/metoo) derudover havde vi i går besøg af forsker mille mortensen (👉🏼millemortensen.dk) , der med afsæt i sit omfattende feltarbejde på rigshospitalet gjorde os klogere på, hvad der gør, at krænkende handlinger og mobning kan finde sted på arbejdspladsen. vi var også i selskab med meta louise foldager, der indførte os i sit arbejde med bl.a. at have flere retningslinjer på filmsettet, når der skal laves intime scener og henviste her til, at hbo går i front og fremover vil hyre “intimacy coordinators” for at sikre mere tryghed. tak til vores brugergruppe for at være med til at sætte fokus på så spændende og relevante emner og for at deltage i går 🙏🏻😘

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
but wylie wasn’t just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: “information operations”, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us military’s doctrine of the “five-dimensional battle space”. his brief ranged across the scl group – the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it.
.
- it’s like dirty mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.’
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer – the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates – and his daughter rebekah.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
warning: this is a graphic story of alleged child trafficking and rape by one of hollywood’s top directors. i am sharing because too few people will share. child sex abuse and trafficking of young boys (and girls) is a dark secret of american society that must be brought to light in order for change to occur.

the line that will stay with me? “metoo - only i was a kid”. #childtrafficking #metoo #iwasakid #bryansinger 
https://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2019/03/bryan-singers-accusers-speak-out/580462/  we spent 12 months investigating various lawsuits and allegations against singer. in total, we spoke with more than 50 sources, including four men who have never before told their stories to reporters. a man we’ll call eric told us that he was 17 in 1997 when he and singer had sex at a party at the director’s house; another we’ll call andy says he was only 15 that same year, when he and singer had sex in a beverly hills mansion. both men say singer, who was then in his early 30s, knew they were under 18, the age of consent in california. (they asked the atlantic to conceal their identity for fear of retaliation, and because they didn’t want certain details about their past made public.) the portrait of singer that emerges is of a troubled man who surrounded himself with vulnerable teenage boys.
the accusations against singer cover a spectrum. some of the alleged victims say they were seduced by the director while underage; others say they were raped. the victims we interviewed told us these experiences left them psychologically damaged, with substance-abuse problems, depression, and ptsd. when asked for comment, singer’s lawyer, andrew b. brettler, noted that singer has never been arrested for or charged with any crime, and that singer categorically denies ever having sex with, or a preference for, underage men. (he also disputed specific details in this story, as noted throughout.).

text:
it's so easy to go outwards and look for outside validation and acceptance. 
when you realize the battle and war outside has nothing to do with the internal struggles of shame and guilt and trauma... i have decided to change the language that's repeated to myself with the shame and guilt and trauma.

i am worthy.
i am my hero.
i am beautifully unbroken.

this court case too shall pass. 
the outcome will not define me. 
i will continue to persevere and help right the wrongs.

#metoo
#metoomovement
#billc337 
#calm

text:
depression doesn't have a face.
.
i saw humans without any humanity. i was hurt. i was alone. i always feel alone. for 5 years i have the symptoms of depression. i had suicidal urge... but that smile never leaves my face. who could know?  i hated everyone. i took drugs... alcohol. i hate myself. i became a mother. but i was alone ... again... single mom.. i stopped feeding myself! i put myself in danger. the only thing that pushed me to get up was my son. his happiness was the only reason for my existence. so i asked for help. because i love him. i see a psychologist. i surround myself only with positive people. i love people! i eat. i'm clean. i'm alive. but depression is hard to beat. i hope to say "i'm cured" one day. you're not alone. you're not bad. ask for help please!
.
j'ai vu des humains sans aucune humanité. j'ai été blessée. j'ai été seule. je me sens toujours seule. depuis 5 ans j'ai les symptômes de la dépression. j'ai eu des envie de suicide... mais ce sourire n'a jamais quitté mon visage. qui pouvait savoir? je détestait tout le monde. j'ai pris de la drogue... beaucoup d'alcool. je me déteste. je suis devenue maman. mais j'étais seule... encore... maman solo... j'ai arrêté de me nourrir. je me suis mise en danger. la seule chose qui me poussait à me lever était mon fils. son bonheur était la seule raison de mon existence. donc j'ai demandé de l'aide. parce que je l'aime. je vois un psy. je m'entoure de personnes positives. j'aime les gens! je mange. je suis clean. je suis en vie ! mais la dépression est dure à battre. j'espère pouvoir dire un jour que je suis guérie. tu n'es pas seul. tu n'es pas mauvais. demande de l'aide stp!! #depression #faceofdepression #depressiondoesnthaveaface #dépression #smile #sourire #maman #mamansolo #singlemom #bloggermom #metoo #stopsexualviolence #anorexiementale #anorexiarecovery #psychologue #psychologist #positif #motivation #yourenotalone #askforhelp #tunespasseul

text:
just. ice. 
that’s what i experienced last year, my abuser’s criminal defender suggesting that perhaps i was making up my claims against him, that i was only out to ruin a man’s reputation. then, said man proved me right by (allegedly🙄) ringing the next girl’s neck too. so now, months after my frustrating learning-curve with the legal system and the point at which i switched focus from the worthless to the worthy (see @andnowsherises), i found myself back in the government center. 
this time, i’m hoping for justice.

and this hope isn’t solely for me or for any women who hold police reports like mine. it’s for those who haven’t been hurt yet. 
yet is the key word there. 
abusers don’t spontaneously stop abusing. a ream of studies show their behavior isn’t caused by circumstances like a bad argument or being drunk, though they’d like us to believe so. instead, psychologists (and yours truly) have come to understand they’re developmentally-scarred bullies who lack an inner sense of #power. their issue is the saddest kind of sad, but the fact that they make 1 in 4 women into victims, that they batter us and assert coercive control for the purpose of feeling powerful, ought to make us all mad. 
mad enough to pay attention. a 2004 study about recidivism in domestic abusers by the center for court innovation showed that “from the moment of arrest to two years post-release, 62% of defendants were rearrested.” and rap sheets that started with misdemeanors often became more serious felony assaults. 
quick, think of your 4 favorite women. which 1 would you be okay with getting assaulted? if you don’t accept that question––and i don’t––then don’t accept a behavior that is predictable and preventable.
.
for more info on holding batterers accountable and an intervention program designed to help, go to emergedv.com #survivorspeaks #seedv #dvawareness #metoo #breakthesilence #breakthecycle #nomoreabuse #getupstandup #womensupportingwomen #howitribe #saveasister #survivorstrong #empowerista #warriorwomen // a thousand kisses to katey for helping me #standstrong

text: memes? yes. memes on couture? yaaass. 🙌🏼 the @viktorandrolf show at paris couture week pretty much summarised the global #mood of 2018.  in larger than life tulle gowns (which in our opinion only @beyonce can pull off), a parade of models walked the runway in sassy slogans. we saw insta favourites “i’m not shy, i just don't like you” and “i am my own muse” and they #woke us up this am. 😳 there was also the ultimate #lazygirl motto “sorry i'm late, i didn’t want to come” and a resounding “no” - likely a bold narrative around the #metoo movement and #consent. the #dutch duo have always been open to experimenting - but as we all know, fashion is a reflection of pop culture, politics and the world we live in - so there was no other way to re-affirm these moods than through this dramatic #runway #experience. we shooook! 🔥😵🤷🏽‍♀️ #fashionweek #pariscoutureweek #paris #pfw

text:
svensk live’s pris för årets insats går till @miaskaringerlazar! motiveringen lyder: 
hon visste exakt vad hon gjorde samma sekund hon aktivt valde att dela med sig av egna erfarenheter i samband med att #metoo startade i sverige. 
en förebild och budbärare för miljontals människor, framförallt kvinnor, som fått nog av patriarkatet och som numera kräver den plats i samhället som borde varit självklar redan från mänsklighetens uppståndelse. 
positionen som en av landets främsta opinionsbildare har stärkts ytterligare genom höstens tv-serie ”kroppshets” och den egna föreställningen ”avig maria - no more fucks to give”. båda är en hyllning till kvinnan och sätter ord på de snedvridna normer som finns i vårt samhälle. 
#miaskäringer #nmftg #blixtenco

text:
oggi sono tornata
li’ dove l’ orologio si fermava
e gli occhi non volevano guardare
ho visto una donna dal capo coperto
con i pensieri smarriti e senza parlare
ci siamo abbracciate con gli occhi.
ho rivisto me 
quando avevo bisogno di speranza
e di qualcuno che mi dicesse
“ insieme fa meno male”
anna gisonda #poesia #insiemefamenomale #oncologia #tumorealseno #metoo #leguerrieresciencesartsandevents

text:
if you are here, then there is a reason. please trust & follow this path. .
.
for some affected by trauma, who in the early phases of healing, those individuals might find this concept by eckhart tolle to be a very difficult one to comprehend.

for those individuals,  i implore you to pause for a moment. .
.
take a deep breath. take another deep breath this time much more controlled & slower. repeat. .
.
take notice of what triggers might be surfacing as a result of a possible hypervigilant "fight or flight" response such as rapid heart beat, anxiousness, sweaty palms, racing thoughts, tension, etc, & be open to understanding that if this is happening to you right now, then what happened to you ... aka ... trauma ... is stealing your joy, your breath, your life, your freedom.
.
it took me a lot of years of deep intense spiritual healing on myself for me to fully understand what this truly means. .
.
what i've stubbornly learned is that we can't be living in accordance w/ our soul if we remain stuck in the loops of our old traumas. .
.
i did a four part series followed by a series of classes called "today i bless my junk" in response to this looped "victimhood" to shed light on the suppressed gifts that came out as a result of my own traumas - attempted abduction, rape, sexual harassment, domestic abuse. .
.
you can visit my youtube channel to watch the episodes 
https://youtu.be/ymhvoahrkxk

or visit my website for the blogs including 5 reasons why you need to bless your junk http://laurahealingwithspirit.com/5-reasons-why-you-need-to-bless-your-junk/

either way, once you can fully comprehend these words by eckhart tolle, you are on the path to living a more joyful soulful life free from that looped victimhood. .
.
i'm here to help guide you. book a session w/ me if my work resonates with you. i have openings this monday, 1/28/19. .
.
with love & appreciation, 
laura
www.laurahealingwithspirit.com 
@laura_healing_with_spirit

text:
my father was an abuser—sexual abuse. i was the youngest of five kids. my earliest memory is me at four years old, outside my sister’s room, trying to go in there and stop what he was doing. i didn’t understand what he was doing, i just knew it didn’t feel right.
.
at 13-14 year old, i was going to principals, teachers, judges… anyone who would listen to me. ‘this is what my father is doing. i need help!’ no one believed me, no one.
.
my father took me to a police station. he was pressing charges against me for trying to hurt him. i have never done anything to my father other than trying to stop him. within the next few days, i had to go before the courts, and the courts decided to put me in a children’s home. they still weren’t going to do anything against my dad. they were just locking me up.
.
when i was 17, i had two full time jobs, money in the bank, and was supporting myself. i applied for emancipation and got it. i came to columbus, got an apartment, met my husband the same day, and have never been apart a day since.
.
my husband tried to help put my family back together, until he realized what i had gone through. fast forward a few years, and i started to put me back together. i don’t condone what my father did. however, i thank him because he made me the strong woman that i am today. he made me the person that would not stand down when i knew something wasn’t right. he made me understand that you have to fight for what you believe in, and for the life that you want.
.
my father has since passed away. i never had the chance to make amends with him. but i realized i didn’t need to make amends with him, i needed to make amends with myself. on many levels i felt that i had failed. the truth of it is, i was the only one that had succeeded. i was the only one that was willing to stand up.

text:
we don’t have to politicise every act of #violence against a woman. it may relieve the anger and sadness to cry “this must stop”, or to blame the #patriarchy, or to, as writer clementine ford did after the #horrific #murder of saiia #maasarwe last week, demand men “pick a side” because “you are all implicated”.
.
.
but it doesn’t help.
.
.
barely a day after maasarwe’s body was found in #bundoora in #melbourne’s north, allegedly the victim of a random #killer (a 20-year-old man has been charged with her rape and murder), the 21-year-old #palestinian’s death was grist for the #gender #culture wars, a pointless loop of generalisation, accusation and defensiveness.
.
.
a few days before, there was a flurry about the gillette’s “the best men can be” advertisement and what it said about masculinity in the age of #metoo. that was all good fun – and there were some important points made, too – but this was about a murder of a young #exchange #student. some things are too serious for a hot take, too #heartbreaking to be seized upon as #evidence for well-worn positions
.
.
.
https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2019/jan/23/its-a-false-comfort-to-say-the-and-of-women-is-caused-by-sexism

text:
dear future lover, 
i don't know how broken i will be when i meet you, whether i will meet you, but i am writing this letter to you.

this isn't the list of things you should be, because this isn't a slam book, where you write about the perfect guy. i am not writing this to you, so that you prepare yourself, just like you prepare yourself for an examination. because, you can never be prepared for love, since it has no prescribed syllabus.

i just want you to know that when you come into my life, help me pick up all the pieces of it. by then, there will be too many for me to pick up. alone. i want you to believe in me then, even  in my worst state. and accept me the way i am. accept me with my scars, my wounds, and do not heal them. just be proud of them

i do not want you to heal my broken heart, because i can do it myself once i pick up the pieces.

today, when i stand alone, with no one by my side, i want to believe in you. because, belief in you, would lead me to belive myself.

maybe you don't exist. maybe you are just a reassuring mirage in a desert. yet you are a reminder that the oasis does exist. 
and even if you don't exist, i believe that you will. 
because, belief is my weapon now.
.
.
saptaparna.
(@randomly__mysterious_)
.
.
.

text:
@gillette is under scrutiny for their new #thebestmencanbe campaign targeting toxic masculinity and encouraging men to part-take in changing the narrative. 🙋🏽‍♂️
-
“it featured men stopping bullying. it showed them stepping in when other men were catcalling women. it addressed the #metoo movement—not by dancing around it with euphemisms, but with plain words: ‘sexual harassment.’ it reminded us that young boys are looking up to grown men to model good and moral behavior. the message was clear: being “a man” didn’t equate to being a bully or a harasser. it meant rejecting the age-old saying of, ‘boys will be boys.’ being a man meant standing up for what’s right. 👏🏽
-
i don’t believe the commercial is hating all men. it’s not saying all men are toxic. it’s simply encouraging all men to call out and check this type of behavior if they see it. it’s asking men to be champions for their mothers, partners, daughters—and their fathers, brothers, and male friends. but to be honest, i’m not surprised at the polarized response. the fact that so many men feel offended by such a seemingly simple notion speaks to how far-reaching and ingrained toxic masculinity is. it speaks to how essential reflection and growth are to every man”— @virenshinde_ ✊🏽
-
solutions are created by communities recognizing a problem and making an effort to change it’s cause.🙌🏽
-
brown boy @virenshinde shares his take on the ads “controversy,” link in bio! 📌
-
what are your thoughts on the ad? tell us in the comments below! 💭 - 🎨 @zhkdesigns ✨
-

text: hitting him where it hurts! it’s a tried-and-true tactic — have a misbehaving child? take away his tv privileges. or his state of the union address. thank you #nancypelosi for keeping the focus where it should be: on the 800,000+ federal workers are now going without multiple paychecks [including some legally required to still work] and countless other americans are feeling the residual effects of this painful and dumb #trumpshutdown. out of touch and just plain cruel. donald #trump: reopen the government now! but, why exactly is our government shutdown over american taxpayers paying for the wall — when #mexico is supposed to be paying for the wall? i don't give a crap about his fan’s spins and interpretations of what he meant to say, or what he really means… he said: "i will build a great wall -- and nobody builds walls better than me, believe me --and i'll build them very inexpensively. i will build a great, great wall on our southern border, and i will make mexico pay for that wall. mark my words." words…marked. he was very clear and specific. he even put it in writing! he wants money for his stupid wall?…it's going to have to be in pesos. end of discussion. #democrats now control of the house and will put forth sensible legislation to benefit the people of this country. and, for the first time, will conduct real congressional oversight of #trump…his life will now [and deservedly so] become a virtual and perpetual deep colonoscopy…the saudis. abuse of power. corruption. ethics. kavanaugh. tax returns. obstruction of justice. #russia….you name it…we'll really start getting to the bottom of it…all! to save #america we must hold to account the inept, corrupt and amoral unindicted co-conspirator in the oval office: #illegitimate #failingpresident #donaldtrump. #washingtondc #lovetrumpshate #nevertrump #msnbc #foxnews #cnn #journalism #moveon #trumpprotest #notmypresident #politics #journalism #indivisible #makeamericagreatagain #womensmarch #crazytown #metoo #bluewave #maga

text:
после невероятно занятых рабочих будней я решила вернуться на просторы интернет-пространства с одной очень противоречивой темой - феминизм в латинской америке. на фото - дом объединения всех боливийских феминистских движений. немного гламурный и даже волшебный, он был создан как некий «храм», в который может обратиться каждая жертва домашнего насилия...домашнее насилие в xxi веке⁉️в европейских странах скорее - лишь редкое явление, а здесь воспринимается зачастую как ежедневная обыденность.
.
кстати, 2017й стал годом тревожных цифр и ещё одним годом борьбы женщин за свои права. это был год, когда латинская америка проголосовала против гендерного насилия, а феминистское движение распространилось по всему региону, соединяя мосты с женскими движениям по всему миру. .
тогда англоязычный словарь «merriam webster» выбрал слово «феминизм» в качестве слова 2017 года, а американский журнал «time» выбрал кампанию #metoo, в рамках которой тысячи женщин поделились личными историями сексуального насилия, «человеком года».
.
в 2017 году я следила за многими из движений, потрясших латинскую америку: .
⚠️41 девочка погибла в огне в государственном детском приюте на окраине города в гватемале ⚠️независимая инициатива открытых данных, целью которой является картография фемицидов в мексике (с 2016 по 2017 года было зарегистрировано 1824 случая фемицида)
⚠️целое движение, последовавшее за студентом из школы медицины университета асуньона в парагвае, раскрыло сложную и мощную сеть, которая ставила под угрозу успешную карьеру многих студенток-медиков.
⚠️в 2017 году участники конкурса красоты «мисс перу» вышли на сцену, обратив внимание общественности  на тревожное количество случаев насилия в отношении женщин в их стране. .
в прошлом году я немного отошла от темы феминизма, однако, попав в этот дом в ла-пасе вновь начала обращаться к тревожной статистике. сегодня я решилась начать эту драматичную тему в рамках рубрики #notes_латиноамериканиста
. 
очень прошу, откликнитесь в комментариях: будете ли вам время от времени интересно читать такие заметки❓и что вы думаете о феминистских движениях❓сталкивались ли вы с этой темой❓
p.s.: мне правда очень интересно узнать ваше мнение🙏🏻

text:
invitation to biennial artists: use wagency to withhold content in support of whitney staff

this fee request is an example of what withholding content from the 2019 whitney biennial would look like using wagency. artists may include any message they like, but the request will appear to the recipient as it does below. fee requests are sent to recipients from w.a.g.e. on behalf of wagents. it reads:

dear adam d. weinberg, scott rothkopf, and the leadership of the whitney museum, 
please find the fee request for my participation in the 2019 whitney biennial below. the total cost of my labor has been calculated according to w.a.g.e.’s minimum standards of compensation. 
my participation in the exhibition is also contingent upon the fulfillment by leadership of the demands made by whitney staff as detailed below and quoted directly from an internal letter sent to you on november 26, 2018. they are as follows: •​for leadership to convey our concerns to the board, including that they consider asking for warren kanders’ resignation.
•​a public statement from the whitney in response to the hyperallergic article
•​a museum wide staff forum for employees to discuss this and other issues, and related policies moving forward
•​the development and distribution of a clear policy around trustee participation.
(nb: here, we intend to clarify what qualifies or disqualifies a wealthy philanthropic individual for the board. is there a moral line? if so, what is that line? if this was an instance of a #metoo scandal, would we call for resignation? if this was an instance of overt racism, would we call for resignation? we believe the line should be that we not be afflicted with any board member whose work or actions are at odds with the museum’s mission.) i add to these demands that leadership establish a reasonable timeline for their fulfillment. 
thank you for your consideration, i look forward to working with you. 
signed,
wagent x

https://wageforwork.com/wagency#top

text:
antes de iniciar, gostaríamos de compartilhar que a nossa publicação não tem intuito de definir o que é feminismo. oh my no! entendemos que são inúmeras leituras, diferentes releituras e muitas possibilidades do entender o que é feminismo para nós, para você, para o mundo.
.
um dos pontos que mais nos agrada é que hoje o podemos vivenciar de forma macro, em consonância com sororidade: ampla rede de apoio, suporte, a qualquer mulher independente do estilo de vida, escolhas ou contexto. com este olhar, trazemos apontamos e reflexões para construirmos juntos o nosso olhar.
.
o movimento dos anos 1970 não existe hoje nos mesmos moldes. a busca pelos direitos das mulheres caminha em vários sentidos, olhares e necessidades. acontece de maneira mais abrangente, de certa fragmentada, até descontruída. não acreditamos que o feminismo deve ser formatado em tamanho único, por única causa, único olhar. esta diversidade fortalece, amplia e aprofunda os debates engajando etnias, religiões, orientação sexual.
.
nunca foi tão fecundo conversar sobre o ser mulher! na mídia tradicional, virtual, nos ambientes de debates, as próprias mulheres nunca estiveram tão unidas e fortalecidas pelas suas causas. #metoo, #nenhumaamenos, #aculpanaoedela, #nehumdireitoamenos são algumas das ações que ganham força pela adesão do universo feminino e por homens que assumem esta causa como sua também.
.
o discurso de emma watson em 2014 é inesquecível! como embaixadora da boa vontade da onu mulheres, lança a campanha #heforshe que promove a igualdade de gênero e empoderamento de mulheres. o desejo de engajar meninos e homens pelas novas relações de gênero sem atitudes ou comportamentos machistas.
.
é essencialmente importante entendermos que não são apenas nos grandes movimentos que feminismo acontece, são todas e pequenas ações que adotamos no dia a dia que fortalece a causa como um todo: você consome marcas produzidas por mulheres? você pratica a sororidade, independente da causa da outra? você contribui com uma educação igualitária a filhos, sobrinhos e afilhados? reflexões para nós, você, para o mundo que desejamos ter. vamos juntos fazer a nossa parte!?
.
.
.
📝 @manoeladubeux

text: non appartengo all'emisfero culturale di fausto #brizzi, anche se ho visto con gusto alcuni suoi #film. ma l'esito della sua vicenda giudiziaria mi rende orgoglioso di aver contestato sin da subito quella grande cialtronata violenta che è il movimento #metoo, succursali #italiane comprese. le molestie sono una cosa orribile, ma lo è parimenti la guerra antropologica al #maschio. e lo sono anche tanti pentimenti tardivi di quante sono corree del metodo -purtroppo antico- della concessione di sè per ottenere favori, opportunità,  e avanzamenti di carriera. il confine tra costrizione e adesione a volte è sottile, sì, ma comunque sempre visibile. #italy #tv #cinema

text:
📸 by @sokom__
.
thank you @hausoftiffany of @spill_stories for incorporating @taranajaneen’s @ted talk on the me too movement in our schedule for the 2018 woc content creators mashup.
.
✨ tarana burke ✨
.
“my vision for the me too movement is a part of a collective vision to see a world free of sexual violence, and i believe we can build that world. full stop. but in order to get there, we have to dramatically shift a culture that propagates the idea that vulnerability is synonymous with permission and that bodily autonomy is not a basic human right. in other words, we have to dismantle the building blocks of sexual violence: power and privilege. so much of what we hear about the me too movement is about individual bad actors or depraved, isolated behavior, and it fails to recognize that anybody in a position of power comes with privilege, and it renders those without that power more vulnerable. teachers and students, coaches and athletes, law enforcement and citizen, parent and child: these are all relationships that can have an incredible imbalance of power. but we reshape that imbalance by speaking out against it in unison and by creating spaces to speak truth to power. we have to reeducate ourselves and our children to understand that power and privilege doesn't always have to destroy and take -- it can be used to serve and build. and we have to reeducate ourselves to understand that, unequivocally, every human being has the right to walk through this life with their full humanity intact.”
.
me too is a movement, not a moment (2018) #metoo

text_retweet:
repost from @projeto.dalia using @repostregramapp - antes de iniciar, gostaríamos de compartilhar que a nossa publicação não tem intuito de definir o que é feminismo. oh my no! entendemos que são inúmeras leituras, diferentes releituras e muitas possibilidades do entender o que é feminismo para nós, para você, para o mundo.
.
um dos pontos que mais nos agrada é que hoje o podemos vivenciar de forma macro, em consonância com sororidade: ampla rede de apoio, suporte, a qualquer mulher independente do estilo de vida, escolhas ou contexto. com este olhar, trazemos apontamos e reflexões para construirmos juntos o nosso olhar.
.
o movimento dos anos 1970 não existe hoje nos mesmos moldes. a busca pelos direitos das mulheres caminha em vários sentidos, olhares e necessidades. acontece de maneira mais abrangente, de certa fragmentada, até descontruída. não acreditamos que o feminismo deve ser formatado em tamanho único, por única causa, único olhar. esta diversidade fortalece, amplia e aprofunda os debates engajando etnias, religiões, orientação sexual.
.
nunca foi tão fecundo conversar sobre o ser mulher! na mídia tradicional, virtual, nos ambientes de debates, as próprias mulheres nunca estiveram tão unidas e fortalecidas pelas suas causas. #metoo, #nenhumaamenos, #aculpanaoedela, #nehumdireitoamenos são algumas das ações que ganham força pela adesão do universo feminino e por homens que assumem esta causa como sua também.
.
o discurso de emma watson em 2014 é inesquecível! como embaixadora da boa vontade da onu mulheres, lança a campanha #heforshe que promove a igualdade de gênero e empoderamento de mulheres. o desejo de engajar meninos e homens pelas novas relações de gênero sem atitudes ou comportamentos machistas.
.
é essencialmente importante entendermos que não são apenas nos grandes movimentos que feminismo acontece, são todas e pequenas ações que adotamos no dia a dia que fortalece a causa como um todo: você consome marcas produzidas por mulheres? você pratica a sororidade, independente da causa da outra? você contribui com uma educação igualitária a filhos, sobrinhos e afilhados? reflexões para nós, você, para o mundo que desejamos ter. vamos juntos fazer a n

text:
antes de iniciar, gostaríamos de compartilhar que a nossa publicação não tem intuito de definir o que é feminismo. oh my no! entendemos que são inúmeras leituras, diferentes releituras e muitas possibilidades do entender o que é feminismo para nós, para você, para o mundo.
.
um dos pontos que mais nos agrada é que hoje o podemos vivenciar de forma macro, em consonância com sororidade: ampla rede de apoio, suporte, a qualquer mulher independente do estilo de vida, escolhas ou contexto. com este olhar, trazemos apontamos e reflexões para construirmos juntos o nosso olhar.
.
o movimento dos anos 1970 não existe hoje nos mesmos moldes. a busca pelos direitos das mulheres caminha em vários sentidos, olhares e necessidades. acontece de maneira mais abrangente, de certa fragmentada, até descontruída. não acreditamos que o feminismo deve ser formatado em tamanho único, por única causa, único olhar. esta diversidade fortalece, amplia e aprofunda os debates engajando etnias, religiões, orientação sexual.
.
nunca foi tão fecundo conversar sobre o ser mulher! na mídia tradicional, virtual, nos ambientes de debates, as próprias mulheres nunca estiveram tão unidas e fortalecidas pelas suas causas. #metoo, #nenhumaamenos, #aculpanaoedela, #nehumdireitoamenos são algumas das ações que ganham força pela adesão do universo feminino e por homens que assumem esta causa como sua também.
.
o discurso de emma watson em 2014 é inesquecível! como embaixadora da boa vontade da onu mulheres, lança a campanha #heforshe que promove a igualdade de gênero e empoderamento de mulheres. o desejo de engajar meninos e homens pelas novas relações de gênero sem atitudes ou comportamentos machistas.
.
é essencialmente importante entendermos que não são apenas nos grandes movimentos que feminismo acontece, são todas e pequenas ações que adotamos no dia a dia que fortalece a causa como um todo: você consome marcas produzidas por mulheres? você pratica a sororidade, independente da causa da outra? você contribui com uma educação igualitária a filhos, sobrinhos e afilhados? reflexões para nós, você, para o mundo que desejamos ter. vamos juntos fazer a nossa parte!?
.
📝 @manoeladubeux

o movimento dos anos 1970 não existe hoje nos mesmos moldes. a busca pelos direitos das mulheres caminha em vários sentidos, olhares e necessidades. acontece de maneira mais abrangente, de cea fragmentada, até descontruída. não acreditamos que o feminismo deve ser formatado em tamanho único, por única causa, único olhar. esta diversidade foalece, amplia e aprofunda os debates engajando etnias, religiões, orientação sexual.
.
nunca foi tão fecundo conversar sobre o ser mulher! na mídia tradicional, viual, nos ambientes de debates, as próprias mulheres nunca estiveram tão unidas e foalecidas pelas suas causas.     são algumas das ações que ganham força pela adesão do universo feminino e por homens que assumem esta causa como sua também.
.
o discurso de emma watson em 2014 é inesquecível! como embaixadora da boa vontade da onu mulheres, lança a campanha  que promove a igualdade de gênero e empoderamento de mulheres. o desejo de engajar meninos e homens pelas novas relações de gênero sem atitudes ou compoamentos machistas.
.
é essencialmente impoante entendermos que não são apenas nos grandes movimentos que feminismo acontece, são todas e pequenas ações que adotamos no dia a dia que foalece a causa como um todo: você consome marcas produzidas por mulheres? você pratica a sororidade, independente da causa da outra? você contribui com uma educação igualitária a filhos, sobrinhos e afilhados? reflexões para nós, você, para o mundo que desejamos ter. vamos juntos fazer a nossa pae!?
.
