text:
“physical effects run deep. many who have been the victims of sexual assault go untreated as the darkness grows within. it’s vital we as women ban together in activism, creating awareness and prevention.” ~alisa k •
•
•

while sexual assault, including rape, can result in physical trauma, many people who experience sexual assault will not suffer any physical injury.

there’s a huge misconception that suggests the victim of sexual violence is a bruised and battered young woman. the central issue in many cases of rape or other sexual assault is whether or not both parties consented to the sexual activity or whether or not both parties had the capacity to do so. thus, physical force resulting in visible physical injury is not always seen. this stereotype can be damaging because people who have experienced sexual assault but have no physical trauma may be less inclined to report to the authorities or to seek health care. however, women who experienced rape or physical violence by a partner were more likely than people who had not experienced this violence to report frequent headaches, chronic pain, difficulty sleeping, activity limitation, poor physical health, and poor mental health. ▪️▪️▪️▪️▪️
#alisak #creatingchange #empoweredwoman #thesweetcharityproject #sexualassault #abuse #metoo #timesup

text:
​​#историичитателей

здравствуйте. хочу поделиться своей историей жизни. не знаю, насколько она имеет отношение к насилию. но наболело. 
меня волнует отношение нашего общества к людям с ограниченными возможностями здоровья. с недавних пор получила инвалидность. хожу с тростью. 
молоденькие девушки-продавщицы моментально оценивают меня взглядом и не здороваются, полностью игнорируют мое нахождение в их заведении. хотя, когда я имела несколько иную внешность, они докучали своими назойливыми «чем вам помочь, что подсказать», и т.д. водители, увидев, что человек с инвалидностью, стараются проехать мимо. не останавливаются. хотя, каждый пассажир — это деньги для них.

в общественном транспорте школьники и студенты стараются опередить и усесться на места для инвалидов. при приеме на работу фактор вашего здоровья также учитывается. меня, например, вынудили написать заявление об уходе именно по причине моей инвалидности. 
когда наше общество будет готово принять факт, что люди разные?! но каждый имеет право на те же блага, что и другие. это право дано человеку по факту рождения, а не по факту наличия всех конечностей.
=================================

text:
domestic violence laws in california do not protect stepparents!

we did not take her cat. she got a cat for her daughter and now says it's not her cat.  it is solely because debbie has had zero involvement for real (remember every time we tried to share her struggles she said she wanted to be a neutral party even when there was abuse) in her god daughter’s life that she is not in touch with the reality of this situation.

on april 11th the day before i was attacked and nearly strangled to death by my husband’s jealous insecure 6ft tall 180 something pound unstable ex-wife that we worked with a highly qualified therapist. a therapist we all as a family including aurelia felt my stepdaughter required for her emotional well-being. aurelia was fully aware that our first appointment was happening. she left it up to me to find her daughter a therapist.
she always treated me like i was her nanny. i arranged all the dental appointments for both kids too. 
it was at the therapist’s recommendation that we make a temporary shift and bring my stepdaughter to our home full time and begin therapy focusing on my stepdaughter’s relationship with her mother and stepdad so she can feel safe and comfortable in her home again. 
the mom just got her a cat, this is the second cat she has gotten her to get her to want to be at her house more. the first cat became her little brother’s. so the first thing that is said is can i bring my new cat momma just got me? of course we said yes and we took her to get her cat and sent her mom an update on how the therapy appointment went. 
the mom was enraged about the cat. she threatened to come to our house with the police 👮‍♀️ if we didn’t bring it back. what she didn’t say anything about her daughter. so if debbie had a clue she would never say these lies. -
-

#metoo #withyou #feminism #안태근_안희정_사건에_가려지고있어_생존자인_제가_직접_공유합니다
1월23일 있었던 이명행 성폭력 사건에 대한 1차 공판 선고 결과입니다.

법원은 “피고 이명행이 한 차례 벌금형을 처벌받은 바 있으며, 대부분의 성희롱 성폭행 사실에 대해 인정하였으나 피해 당사자들과 합의하지 못한 점, 수차례 동일한 범행으로 재범의 우려가 크다는 점, 수사 과정에서 자신의 행위를 연애 감정이라 강변한 점, 피해자의 경험과 기억이 이명행의 진술과 매우 상반된 점” 에 주목하였으며, 징역 8월과 40시간 성폭력 예방교육 수강, 아동 관련사업장 3년간 취업 제한을 선고, 도주 우려로 구속 명령되었습니다. 
이명행이 다수의 피해자들에게 저지른 끔찍한 범죄 행위에 비하면 법원이 내린 선고는 미미합니다만, 법원이 그의 범죄 행위를 대부분 인정하고 짧지만 징역을 선고한 것은 매우 의미 있는 결과입니다. 
피해자들은 위와 같은 법원의 판단에 용기와 힘을 얻었습니다. 무엇보다 연극계 동료들이 보내 준 탄원서는 희망과 연대의 힘을 피부로 느끼게 해주었다며 성폭력반대연극인행동을 통해 감사의 말씀 전해 오셨습니다. 여러분, 감사합니다. 
그러나 우리는 가해자들이 법원에서 눈물로 선처를 호소하면서도, 항소를 거듭하는 모습을 목격했습니다. 앞으로도 피해자들과 함께 소리 높여 주십시오. 지금보다 더 크게, 더 멀리 그리고 더 깊이 울려 퍼질 수 있도록 여러분의 변함없는 지지와 연대가 필요합니다. 
마지막으로, 연극계 미투 운동의 시작이었던 이명행 피해자 여러분께 이루 말할 수 없는 존경과 감사하는 마음을 전합니다. 여러분 덕분에 우리는 많은 일들을 할 수 있었습니다. 그리고 해낼 것입니다. 
끝까지 함께 하겠습니다. 
2019년 1월 24일
성폭력반대연극인행동

text:
“anticipation” runs from now till mar 2: in the age of social identity politics world-wide shifting from inclusion to division, the recent d&g scandal on the chinese people, the #metoo movement etc, the need to dismantle discrimination barriers continue to dominate the headlines. the role of an artist and of a gallery is not to enjoy the splendid isolation outside of this mainstream conversation, but to channel, amplify and dissect the issues that drive it. artists themselves, both male and female, will respond to the debate in their own way. as art synthesizes and distills the news cacophony into its essential note, the result, we believe, will be a message of unity rather than division.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text: your reminder of who’s to blame for shutting down our government. it’s all about you donald #trump! you offered to “take the mantle” on december 11, 2018 — it’s all about you — and only you! day 34…you now are responsible for the longest shutdown in u.s. history. you blew away the [one and only] shutdown under #obama and surpassed the record for longest government shutdown — topping the 21 day shutdown under bill clinton. 800,000+ federal workers are now going without multiple paychecks [including some legally required to still work] and countless other americans are feeling the residual effects of this painful and dumb #trumpshutdown. out of touch and just plain cruel. reopen the government now! but, why exactly is our government shutdown over american taxpayers paying for the wall — when #mexico is supposed to be paying for the wall? text:
друзья!😎 на этой неделе вы могли задать свой вопрос двукратному бронзовому призёру олимпийских игр 2008, двукратному чемпиону мира, европы и россии по прыжкам в воду, директору сшор по прыжкам в воду "мгфсо" москомспорта - глебу гальперину @glebdiving 👍🏻
⠀
мы отобрали лучшие вопросы на которые ответил глеб:
⠀
❓глеб расскажи случались у тебя в карьере, на тренировке или на соревнованиях не удачные входы в воду и расскажи какого это не удачно войти в воду с 10 метров ?😱🤣👌🤘
⠀
➡️​«знаю что этот вопрос задал мой хороший друг олимпийский чемпион по тяжелой атлетике дмитрий берестов. ответ таков «это как упасть с 10 метров на асфальт - только не умираешь»)))) шутка!!!! если серьезно, ничего страшного для прыгуна в воду в этом нет, гораздо опаснее уронить себе 200 килограммовую штангу на голову))))»
⠀
❓‌короткая стрижка - это профессиональная прическа у прыгунов?
⠀
➡️«я так думаю что это просто удобство. где то 80% ребят в прыжках в воду с короткой стрижкой, много плюсов после бассейна, фактически не надо вытирать голову, сушить ее чтобы не простыть! штаны одел и пошел))»
⠀
⭕️продолжение в нашей группе вконтакте (ссылка в шапке профиля)
⠀

text:
time for some relaxed, non-posed bodies on instagram.
.
.
i'm tired feeling like a woman's worth in this world is only relevant if she is considered beautiful.
i'm tired of conversations with men always resulting in questions about my relationship status and comments on my appearance.
i'm tired of my chosen independence and solitude, my freedom, being viewed as an open ticket, a space that needs conquering by a man.
the persistant notion that i am looking for something or need something.
.
. 
how about the notion that either or half or whole i am exactly as i need to be in that moment?
how about letting a woman feel whatever she is feeling without the need to provide a solution?
how about letting her own her own physical and mental space, her own energy without trying to occupy this and fill it with your bullshit?
women aren't projects. they aren't your next business venture. your next ornament, entertainer or showcase.
.
.
#dailyfeminism #feminista #femme #feministactivism #toxicmasculinity #womantroubles #alertaalerta #sisters #womensrights #activist #blogosphere #speakmymind #liberation #metoo #thoughtoftheday

i am tired of conversations with men always resulting in questions about my relationship status and comments on my appearance.
i am tired of my chosen independence and solitude, my freedom, being viewed as an open ticket, a space that needs conquering by a man.
the persistant notion that i am looking for something or need something.
.
. 
how about the notion that either or half or whole i am exactly as i need to be in that moment?
how about letting a woman feel whatever she is feeling without the need to provide a solution?
how about letting her own her own physical and mental space, her own energy without trying to occupy this and fill it with your bullshit?
women are not projects. they are not your next business venture. your next ornament, entertainer or showcase.
.
.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
christopher wylie, who worked with a cambridge university academic to obtain the data, told the observer: “we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles. and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.” documents seen by the observer, and confirmed by a facebook statement, show that by late 2015 the company had found out that information had been harvested on an unprecedented scale. however, at the time it failed to alert users and took only limited steps to recover and secure the private information of more than 50 million individuals.

the data was collected through an app called thisisyourdigitallife, built by academic aleksandr kogan, separately from his work at cambridge university. through his company global science research (gsr), in collaboration with cambridge analytica, hundreds of thousands of users were paid to take a personality test and agreed to have their data collected for academic use.

however, the app also collected the information of the test-takers’ facebook friends, leading to the accumulation of a data pool tens of millions-strong. facebook’s “platform policy” allowed only collection of friends’ data to improve user experience in the app and barred it being sold on or used for advertising. the discovery of the unprecedented data harvesting, and the use to which it was put, raises urgent new questions about facebook’s role in targeting voters in the us presidential election. it comes only weeks after indictments of 13 russians by the special counsel robert mueller which stated they had used the platform to perpetrate “information warfare” against the us.

carole cadwalladr & emma graham-harrison
the guardian

text:
today, there is much debate surrounding senator joni ernst’s announcement. there are numerous “ah ha gotcha” comments on twitter regarding her statement. however, i believe her and admire the courage and strength it took for her to tell her story. sexual violence is an issue that affects everyone, and while preventative legislation such as the vawa can help to dissipate the issue, the problem of sexual and domestic abuse is so much bigger than partisanship politics. while i do not condone her statements and behavior during the kavanaugh hearing, i absolutely believe her and stand behind her as a survivor. no one deserves sexual assault. no one deserves domestic abuse. no one. my hope is that she will go forward and use her position of power to advocate for survivors and work to help victims in similar situations. nonetheless, i believe her story. please have some compassion for her experience and remember that name-calling and harassing tactics are not the solutions to this issue. 
i am linking the original article in our bio. please read it. every story a survivor chooses to share is an essential one. •

today, there is much debate surrounding senator joni ernst’s announcement. there are numerous “ah ha gotcha” comments on twitter regarding her statement. however, i believe her and admire the courage and strength it took for her to tell her story. sexual violence is an issue that affects everyone, and while preventative legislation such as the vawa can help to dissipate the issue, the problem of sexual and domestic abuse is so much bigger than paisanship politics. while i do not condone her statements and behavior during the kavanaugh hearing, i absolutely believe her and stand behind her as a survivor. no one deserves sexual assault. no one deserves domestic abuse. no one. my hope is that she will go forward and use her position of power to advocate for survivors and work to help victims in similar situations. nonetheless, i believe her story. please have some compassion for her experience and remember that name-calling and harassing tactics are not the solutions to this issue.

text: i’ve been traveling for over 5 weeks now and i finally hit a wall. kristina and i took a 7 hr bus ride from budapest to prague, upon arrival i was so mentally/physically exhausted, i couldn’t possibly think about sightseeing. we found a pub near tina’s, excited to watch the saints and feel a little connection to home, only to watch them get robbed by shittyyyy calls. i also got into an argument with the owner of the bar over the #metoo movement, specifically the gillette ad, calling him out for perpetuating bullshit patriarchal views and having a fragile ego and was almost certain i would get kicked out. needless to say, i was on one, and kristina is a trooper for putting up with my punk ass. when we lost, i cried actual tears - who am i? - cuz i was so ready to be home feeling the energy of new orleans. but my last visit to prague was wasted on a rainy weekend 10 years ago, mostly spent escaping the cold by drinking beer in our hostel, followed by nursing college hangovers and missing out on everything the city has to offer. so i was determined to use that eclipse energy to get a good night sleep and enjoy the city as much as i could. our list of activities was enormous (shoutout to @elishawillems, @flava_flaim & @tinan9 for carefully curating our week!), impossible to even scratch the surface. we spent days strolling the streets, trying to see as much as possible. we wandered in and out of old town, finding ourselves returning to admire the breathtaking views of the charles bridge until our frozen fingers needed to be thawed by mulled wine. pretty sure mulled wine is the only way to warm up - at least the only way i want. prague is easily one of the most beautiful places i’ve been, with centuries old architecture and color for days. and an endless supply of cold beer and places to enjoy it! the highlight was getting to experience tina’s life in prague, meeting her czech friends and enjoying some of her favorite spots. we’ve gotten really good at finding hip hop clubs and dancing way past reasonable hours but i wouldn’t have it any other way. prague re-energized me in a way i wouldn’t have imagined, physically and spiritually, so we continue on! na zdravi!
name: Chelsea Krant

text_retweet:
#repost @wageforwork ・・・
invitation to biennial artists: use wagency to withhold content in support of whitney staff

this fee request is an example of what withholding content from the 2019 whitney biennial would look like using wagency. artists may include any message they like, but the request will appear to the recipient as it does below. fee requests are sent to recipients from w.a.g.e. on behalf of wagents. it reads:

dear adam d. weinberg, scott rothkopf, and the leadership of the whitney museum, 
please find the fee request for my participation in the 2019 whitney biennial below. the total cost of my labor has been calculated according to w.a.g.e.’s minimum standards of compensation. 
my participation in the exhibition is also contingent upon the fulfillment by leadership of the demands made by whitney staff as detailed below and quoted directly from an internal letter sent to you on november 26, 2018. they are as follows: •​for leadership to convey our concerns to the board, including that they consider asking for warren kanders’ resignation.
•​a public statement from the whitney in response to the hyperallergic article
•​a museum wide staff forum for employees to discuss this and other issues, and related policies moving forward
•​the development and distribution of a clear policy around trustee participation.
(nb: here, we intend to clarify what qualifies or disqualifies a wealthy philanthropic individual for the board. is there a moral line? if so, what is that line? if this was an instance of a #metoo scandal, would we call for resignation? if this was an instance of overt racism, would we call for resignation? we believe the line should be that we not be afflicted with any board member whose work or actions are at odds with the museum’s mission.) i add to these demands that leadership establish a reasonable timeline for their fulfillment. 
thank you for your consideration, i look forward to working with you. 
signed,
wagent x

http://wageforwork.com/wagency/2019-whitney-biennial#top
https://wageforwork.com/wagency#top

text:
a true man-
i walk with the strength of true love within every part of my being
looking at all as though they are apart of onesness
always looking for the beauty in others
humbled strength from an awakened soul i am
passionate 
tender
present
i have no desire to destroy, but to intertwine in harmony 
my thoughts are driven by love and it’s highest places 
within me is a heart that beats as yours
invited
asked
being
my love for woman whispers louder then the worlds screams
my actions driven by my spirit, with nature in tow
in me no lies, but loves deepest passion awaiting
 i am strength, i am power, i am passion, i am love, i am-a true man -travis escalante

text:
〰️ coup de cœur 〰️
@lesdessinsdevicdoux jeune illustratrice que l’on a rencontré lors de notre première dînette, a participé à notre collab’ « 2019 année de la meuf » 💕
on lui a demandé quels étaient ses projets pour 2019 et ce que représente pour elle cette nouvelle année ⬇️
.
ses projets 2019 « arriver à partager ma semaine entre illustration et journalisme (mon premier métier, que j’aimerais reprendre). je souhaite que cette année soit celle de la professionnalisation de mes dessins. je rêve de pouvoir illustrer des articles et un jour faire une expo de mes illustrations.
j’ai aussi un projet de podcast, j’aimerais donner la parole à des femmes et hommes de toutes les générations afin qu’il me racontent et me parlent de leur première fois (sexuelle)! une belle occasion de parler rapport au corps, amour etc. » 🙌🏻 on te souhaites pleins de réussite victoire, tous tes projets sont géniaux !
.
« 2019, c’est une nouvelle année de combat pour les droits des femmes mais aussi, après #metoo, une année d’émancipation et de liberté totale. une liberté qui nous permette de nous sentir pleinement nous et de nous réapproprier notre corps comme bon nous semble! ce sont des sujets que j’aime illustrer et je ne m’arrêterai pas cette année. » .
sa joli carte est dispo dans notre pack de 7 cartes (édition limitée)disponible sur notre boutique etsy (lien dans notre bio) ✌🏻
.
📸 @confettisetpoesie 
#illustration #drawing #dessin #2019 #2019anneedelameuf #cartepostale #papeterie #feminisme #femmessingulieres #girlpower

text:
📝history📝: .
.
.
.
i’m always surprised by prejudice. i know that sounds super lame. but just because someone’s gay, assuming they want you to grope them is just so fucking weird to me. i don’t understand some people. at all. i’m doubly sorry for your assault and you facing prejudice. i look forward to a future where people are truly equal and abuse and assault are considered so barbaric, that it’s taboo and doesn’t happen. imagine that. omg that would truly be a great time to be alive. thank you for sending in ‘yourstory’. i hope you’re okay and you continue to be okay❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️. take care of you. -💜❤️vu
.
.

today’s story : a dream job for nidhi  turns into a nightmare as a man in power, her boss decides that he can get away with intimidation and harassment at the workplace. a true story.  this was 15 years ago when there were no systems for workplace harassment in place. today, lakhs of women join the workforce everyday and after the sc passed the prevention of sexual harassment against women  at the workplace bill in 2013, all companies have to follow a system to stop sexual harassment at the workplace. supreet’s story ends with hope. are you a working woman facing harassment at work? do you want to help someone who is ? do you just want to know about your rights and follow your dream unafraid? does your company have such a policy? catch this story on my brand new audio show on @jiosaavn saavn now. be brave m. kyun ki aapka saath khadi hoon #mainbhi #metoo #nowstreaming #newshow #raiseyourvoice #jiosaavn

text:
in the last six months, our helpline received many #calls from adults who were triggered, or reminded of the #abuse they experienced as a #child. many of these brave callers were victims of incest. almost half (42%) of the callers were male. for some, it was the first time they had told anyone about it. for others, they had tried to tell someone, but were not believed, or belittled for not being "man enough" to get over it. 
we can hear the pain in these brave callers' voices when they disclose what's happened to them. we must do more to help male #survivors heal -- we start by #breakingthestigma that it doesn't happen to men. 
if you or someone you know would like #support or #resources, our helpline is available 24/7 via #text or #phone. 1.800.770.1650 or text 'iowahelp' to 201-21. 
#metoo #mencanbethevictim #childabuse #safety4survivors #survivor #survivor2019 #iowa

text:
i stand with you my little miracles.  i stand with all the little miracles whose lives have been cut short, i stand for all those who think that it is okay to end your life because it's inconvenient to theirs.  there are more for you precious children of god than those that are against you.  we will fight, we will let our voices be heard, we will do the best we can to vindicate your death. 
i rarely post controversial things, but i cannot keep quiet in regards to this.  this is not a post to debate about women's rights etc etc.  without question, this new law is murder!  many of you care more about animals than you do for the lives of these human babies and if that is your thought process...please do not come for me. 
1: if you are not a woman and you make a comment contrary to this, please be ready for war.  i will politely kill you with the kindness of god in whatever form it comes out.
2: if you never wanted children in the first place (male or female) do not even try it...you will never know the pain and the heartache we feel.
3: if you know someone who has had an abortion/thought of having and abortion/currently having an abortion... i am praying for you that you make the best decision for your child(ren), and then i will pray that the decision made was best for you.  there is a sequence to what i said...(your child...first and you second)... may god have mercy on all of us.

today’s story : a dream job for nidhi  turns into a nightmare as a man in power, her boss decides that he can get away with intimidation and harassment at the workplace. a true story.  this was 15 years ago when there were no systems for workplace harassment in place. today, lakhs of women join the workforce everyday and after the sc passed the prevention of sexual harassment against women  at the workplace bill in 2013, all companies have to follow a system to stop sexual harassment at the workplace. supreet’s story ends with hope. are you a working woman facing harassment at work? do you want to help someone who is ? do you just want to know about your rights and follow your dream unafraid? does your company have such a policy? catch this story on my brand new audio show on @saavn now. be brave m. kyun ki aapka saath khadi hoon #mainbhi #metoo #nowstreaming #newshow #raiseyourvoice #jiosaavn

text:
selections from the withering in bloom series by guest curator @femme_pots on view in enough. reception tomorrow! 6-8pm. free & open to the public.

artist statement (shortened for ig - read in full at the show): “it is as though the toll taken on survivors of sexual assault has been overlooked; it has been passed on generation after generation and dismissed as another obligatory action that women must abide by. our beauty and transcendence camouflages the state of our minds and souls. our environment has become hazardous and those within it allude to the issues at hand out of a need to be perceived as progressive. women are treated as nothing but vessels for seed and should be silenced otherwise. it is time to call attention to this—to look at the foundation and tend to this culmination. this series is meant to confront you, to make you see the withering effects of a society promoting rape and violence against women, and to consider the effects that could take place should this environment change. it is not meant to mistake victims as such: we are survivors adjusting to our surroundings.

turning each piece as my pain and experiences revolve around me, i bloom each from soil. out of nothing being given just as every woman before me, i recycle the earth to create a representation of my state. i emerge from a lost vessel. a vessel that no longer bares your seed for you have stripped that gift away from yourself. i am no longer a form for the taking, i am fragile yet strong in stance and not to be disturbed any further. i have survived the fire and am in a state of new beauty and purpose. i am here to show you that you have wilted me, but i am not subdued. i am not broken from the actions of this nation." #enough #metoo #mcaexhibition

text:
собираетесь побаловать себя походом в кино на этой неделе? я подготовила для вас новый обзор #toreincarnate_movies!
🍿 мария – королева шотландии (2018)
🎬 когда: 17.01
🍿 о чем: юная вдова королева мария (сирша ронан) возвращается из франции в родную шотландию, чтобы править своим народом. по крови мария имеет право на английский трон, который сейчас занимает сестра елизавета (марго робби). 👸🏻👸🏻 любовные интриги и политические заговоры поставят под угрозу оба престола и изменят ход истории. .
🎥 зачем: на режиссерский дебют театральной постановщицы джози рурк все ждали с нетерпением. и рурк не изменила себе: картина "мария – королева шотландии" выглядит и правда больше как постановка, нежели кино с крупным бюджетом. в лучшем понимании этого слова. бескрайние пейзажи "дикой" шотландии и крупные планы от оператора джона мэтисона созвучны с контрастирующими по духу и настроению персонажами марго робби и сиршы ронан. ❤️музыкальное сопровождение гениального макса рихтера завораживает, а от работы оскароносной художницы по костюмам александры бирн (награда за костюмированную драму "золотой век" (2007) с кейт бланшетт в роли елизаветы i) сложно оторвать глаз. 👗
.
конечно, история скандальной королевы марии стюарт до сих пор остается загадкой: как на самом деле развивались события достоверно не известно, а те или иные находки все еще вызывают споры у историков. однако джози рурк решила положить в основу своего фильма роман британского историка джона гая «моя жизнь принадлежит мне: настоящая история марии — королевы шотландии» и достаточно вольно интерпретировать факты. 🤔 именно поэтому фильм про xvi век выглядит в меру прогрессивно – в нем достаточно примеров смены гендерных ролей и размышлений на современные темы. хорошо это или плохо для исторической драмы решает зритель, но явный феминистический посыл картины во времена #metoo совершенно точно играет на руку создателям картины. 👍🏻
.
продолжение в комментариях 👇👇👇

text:
join the creatress @sunsetkava for our sexual healing support group & workshop. this workshop is for women and men who need a safe space & support to heal from their experiences with sexual abuse. we understand that it can be uncomfortable, even terrifying to face our past experiences with sexual abuse. we are here to support you through that fear, anxiety, discomfort, sadness, anger, and anything else that comes up as you take this incredibly brave step toward your healing. the deep sense of relief from release, the empowerment from your courageousness, and the love from supportive peers can bring so much hope and healing that can change our lives in beautiful ways. 
our main objective in this workshop series is to clear the energetic and psychological imprint that sexual trauma may have left on us that affects who we are and how we function in the world. it is so important and necessary that we reclaim our power over our sexuality and over our lives now and for generations to come, so that we may operate from a place of healing rather than a place of hurt. within this safe space, you will have the option to share your experiences and insights openly, write them in your journal or simply listen and work through things internally. this is a judgment-free zone, and a space full of love and healing energy. 
in session 1 we will be:
- identifying where we are now, in terms of our coping mechanisms. how have we been dealing with our pain?
- identifying new ways we can nurture ourselves and heal our pain
- gently recalling our experiences with sexual abuse
- defining "trauma" and identifying our triggers
- practicing new ways to respond to triggers
- identifying our strengths - identifying our support team
- beginning the process of "cord-cutting" (cutting energetic ties from our abuser)
- leading a group meditation
- leading a spiritual cleansing ritual

rsvp at iamthecreatress.com/ourevents (link in bio)

text:
derrière un viol, il y a une victime, qui souffre et qui doit se reconstruire. malheureusement cette reconstitution est parfois entravée par un sentiment de culpabilité complètement injustifié ! quoi que les gens disent, une victime de viol ne dois jamais se sentir coupable ⚠.un viol n’est jamais justifié ! une victime n’est jamais responsable ! on entend encore tropsouvent “elle l’a cherché, t’as vu comment elle était habillée”, “elle avait bu”, “elle l’avaitallumé” … alors que le seul et unique coupable est la personne qui viole ! il faut arrêter deculpabiliser les victimes et ne surtout pas minimiser le rôle du violeur, ne pas lui trouver de
circonstances atténuantes. le viol est un crime et le seul responsable est le violeur !
.
.

text:
такие разные куколки🙌
⠀
куколки различных бабочек сильно отличаются по форме и цвету. обычно они одноцветные и гладкие. но встречаются и куколки с колючими либо узловатыми выступами. некоторые куколки коричневые или зеленые; другие — великолепно окрашены, иногда с золотым или серебряным рисунком.
⠀
отличия так значительны и так характерны для каждого вида, что по куколке можно определить вид бабочки.
⠀
средством защиты куколки от хищников является маскировка. у некоторых видов бабочек цвет куколок зависит от субстрата, на котором окукливалась гусеница🐛

text:
초등학교 도덕시간에 선생님이 보여줬던 영화 goodbye my friend에서 주인공 역이였던 아역배우 ㅂㄹㄷ... ㅂㄹㄷ가 출현한 영화는 다봤고 어떻게 떠나버렸는지는 중학교 들어가서 알았고 어릴때부터 연예계에서 일하는게 악영향이 컷구나라고만 생각했지 이정도일줄은 몰랐다. 
굿바이마이프렌드 후로 본 ‘죽음보다 더 무서운 비밀’ 한때 나치였던 노인의 비밀을 알아버린 소년의 이야기로 어릴때 보고도 좋은영화로 생각했는데(시발 내가 몇번이나 다시봤는데) 뒷일을 아니 속이 매스껍다. ’죽음보다 무서운 비밀’ 감독인 브라이넌 싱어는 당시 13살 이였던 ㅂㄹㄷ를 주변에게 자신의 ‘애인’으로 소개했고 ㅂㄹㄷ가 약물중독에 시달리게된 이유기도 함( ㅂㄹㄷ는 게이or바이도 아니였고 커리어때문이라고 한다)
브라이언 싱어는 수십년간 십대 소년들(아동모델 배우)을 성폭행 강간해 왔고 den이라는 회사를 설립(*파트너들에게 아이들을 ‘공급’도 받음*:페도필), 갈곳없는 어린 동성애자 청소년들을 위한 프로그램을 만든다는 명목으로 대려다 놓고 마약공급 포주노릇을 했다고한다. 심지어 관련되어있던 콜린스 렉터, 게리 고다드는 처벌을 받거나 폭로를 당했으나 당시에도 거물이었던 브라이언싱어는 구렁이 담넘어가듯 피해갔다(이것도 오래전 일) den에 속해있던 아이들은 브라이언 싱어의 파티보이로 불렸고 그들중 실제로 싱어의 영화에 출연한 이도 있고 den에서 지내는 피해자들에게 월급을 줬다고 한다. 싱어에게서 벗어나서도 약물중독에 벗어나지 못해 매춘을 하는등 완전히 인생이 망가져버린 피해자들이 무수하다고.......
ㅅㅂ...토할것같아 가장 어린 이피해자가 12살이야..
찾다보니 익숙한 내용인것 같아 뭐지 했는데 몇년전에도 터져서 알고있는거였다 이새낀지는 몰랐지. 그때 매장당할줄 알았는데 잘도 일 받아먹고 살았구나 일도 내팽개치고 수저만 올리고.. 헐리웃이 포용할수 없는 범죄는 없는것 같은데..?
이미 헐리웃에선 공공연했고 파티보이였던 연예계에서 일하는 사람한텐 너도 파티보이였냐고 찔러보기도 했다고 하고..히야.. 헐리웃에 페도필이 많고 잡히지 않는단건 알았는데 ㅅㅂ
감옥에 들어가자마자 수감자중 하나가 찔러 버렸으면 .
모든 피해자들의 불행은 싱어 책임이고 ㅂㄹㄷ의 죽음도 싱어 책임이다 .
와 이새끼 피해자 한테 감시 붙이고 협박까지했네#childmolester #bryansinger #pedophelia #pedopheliaiswrong #killthepedophile #metoo #withyou #브라이언싱어 #아동성폭력 #아동성범죄 #페도필리아 #미투 #위드유

text:
when people, especially females lose sight of their objectivity due to emotion.

o have a button i can press in my head to switch off my emotions when the gravity of the situation requires. over the lovely little chics i love one of whom is a tender 7 years and some few months and will be greatly impacted by my choices took me a while. fighting for my humanity remember.

one girl had lucky red pants and this guy suggested a preference. i'm not too sure whether he did anything untoward, if not trust a certain wanna be driving instructor so can evidence it as possible.

on the other hand i've directly been involved in a situation where something less than suggestive is said and intentionally misconstrued.

that example 2as a guy trying to tell a girl he had, had bad experiences with females in the past, whilst being culturally oblivious about tactility in thos #metoo abusing era. she retorted, what did you threaten me with. i was like what the f!

this guy says another girl wore red pants and it might work for her; this is all about semantics and you'd have to be there. however telling is the unrelated accusations prior, it doesn't certify guilt but weights heavily against him. he looks dodgy to me.

but this story does underline that what pants you have on, clearly is relevant. and to argue otherwise is to undermine the validity of law and thus make it easier for perpetrators of such offences to escape.

anyone heard that, honesty is usually the best policy?

text:
ritual castings 
the wash (as it seams) @msuunionartgallery 
panty portraits 1 - 5 from the panty project .
the panty project is an ongoing social practice project. participants, womxn and those who identify as womxn, courageously share with me their stories of experienced gendered transgressions and violent aggressions, whether cultural and/or interpersonal. participants write a word or phrase onto the panel of their selected undergarment; i hand-embroider over their mark-making and photograph them as if they have been taken off. this work addresses the inherent misogyny within our language, and the consequential "essestializing" of womxn, which reduces womxn, and those who identify as womxn, to "less than." this work is about healing and transcendence. 
womxn's long-silenced voices must be heard.
.

text:
[recapchrisbrown] alors, il est sorti de gav et reste à paris...
sauf que la fille maintient l'accusation et vient de donner une interview au parisien.
elle a pris un avocat..et passe donc à l'offensive médiatique.

que les choses soient claires, je ne sais pas ce qui s'est passé dans cette chambre d'hôtel....mais le fait que cette femme maintienne sa version, est la pire chose qui aurait pu lui arriver ( et la meilleure à elle s'il l'a fait), car comme dit à plusieurs reprises sur cette page.
les procès ne sont plus judiciaires, mais médiatiques..et en plein #metoo, si une femme t'accuse de viol.
c'est très compliqué de s'en sortir...( et tu n'as pas à le faire d'ailleurs, si tu l'as fait..) c'est d'ailleurs interessant car #justinbieber a pris sa défense hier et s'est vu incendier sur la toile par ses propres fans. les fans de t.i, eux n'ont rien dit...parce que la scission se dessine clairement.

si vous voyez la démographie des fans de j.b et ceux de t.i, vous comprenez où la division se fait.. et c'était d'ailleurs attendu.

et ça revient au parallèle qui sera explicité dans ma prochaine vidéo, et déjà évoqué en début de semaine avec l’article de usa today!

text:
“i was sixteen, working out in an oversized t-shirt and athletic shorts.  all i wanted to do was make it to the end of my cardio, but this man in his mid-60s kept staring at me.  no matter where he went in the gym, he just kept staring at me.  finally, when i was doing sit-ups at the end, he came and stood over me, completely towering over me.  he asked me a bunch of questions about what i was wearing and whether i had a boyfriend.  then he asked me how old i was.  when i told him my age, he nudged me with his leg and said, ‘two more years, baby.’” - shaina

and now a word on the #trumpshutdown for our hypocrite evangelical friends out there who twist themselves into pretzels trying to justify their support of our "charlatan-in-chief"… putting it in terms they might understand. the truth shall set you free!
the truth is, 800,000+ federal workers are now going without multiple paychecks [including some legally required to still work] and countless other americans are feeling the residual effects of this painful and dumb shutdown.
question for you guys to ruminate over coffee after sunday services: 
how many paychecks could you afford to miss before it becomes a problem?
out of touch and just plain cruel.
#trump offered to “take the mantle” on december 11, 2018 — he is solely responsible for the longest shutdown in u.s. history. he blew away the [one and only] shutdown under #obama and surpassed the record for longest government shutdown — topping the 21 day shutdown under bill clinton. but, why exactly is our government shutdown over american taxpayers paying for the wall — when #mexico is supposed to be paying for the wall? i don't give a crap about his fan’s spins and interpretations of what he meant to say, or what he really means… he said: "i will build a great wall -- and nobody builds walls better than me, believe me --and i'll build them very inexpensively. i will build a great, great wall on our southern border, and i will make mexico pay for that wall. mark my words." words…marked. he was very clear and specific. he even put it in writing! he wants money for his stupid wall?…it's going to have to be in pesos. end of discussion. to save #america we must hold to account the inept, corrupt and amoral unindicted co-conspirator in the oval office: #illegitimate #failingpresident #donaldtrump. #washingtondc #lovetrumpshate #nevertrump #msnbc #foxnews #cnn #journalism #moveon #trumpprotest #notmypresident #politics #journalism #indivisible #makeamericagreatagain #womensmarch #crazytown #metoo #bluewave #maga #jesus

note: we do not advocate on politics. however, we do advocate on behalf of all women who are on fire for their dreams and growing inequality.

these women are federal workers and due to the known individual who has allowed his power to negatively take over his thinking process... many families who work hard are in need. this should never happen! 
we need:
•selfless individuals who are leaders
•team players
•role models for all
•listeners & conversations
•compromisers
•caring leaders who knows right from hurt!
•and not just 1 individual who takes 100% control of over 800,000 federal workers, their families, cia, fbi, dhs, dea, national security, must i go on🤷‍♀️ how many people are you willing to publicly hurt through indirect and direct media outlets?? ———————————————————————-
•why is congress and washington staff getting paid? shouldn’t they too be “shutdown” until they can come to a mutual agreement that works for all? ———————————————————————-
•how can a “wall” truly help u.s. citizens when we are the ones in desperate times as a whole..? ———————————————————————-
•why would a federal government worker want to process taxes when they are not getting paid???? who does that?? •i truly 🙏 these hardworking women and men receive monies from many outlets without them paying any interest to anyone. we will have a plan by tomorrow to help some of these women.
———————————————————————
•as a formal federal employee, i know what that is like to sit  in the “not knowing” section. it hurts!
•i truly believe that hurt people, hurt people. please get some help to learn how to be a team player and build character. it helps for business locally and globally 🌎

text:
i spent three nights in stockholm. it was an experience that taught me a lot about human instinct, desire, friendships, and protecting yourself. i was invited to stay with a couchsurfing host who seemed so positive and open but turned into a manipulative sexual predator. i was so uncomfortable. felt harassed and objectified. i ended up leaving in the middle of the night after he tried to take advantage of me. this photo from the hotel i fled to shows determination and resolve not to allow someone to make me a victim. i resolved to find strength in the experience and learn from it. i'm posting this now to share what i hope will give others strength.

#tourdenathan2016 #metoo #couchsurfing #strength #reflection #ihatemyselfie

text:
beldurra sentitzen dut korrika egitera joaten naizenean; beti. batzuetan gutxiago, besteetan gehiago, baina beldurra. ez da arrazionala: badakit probabilitate gutxi daudela berez gizon ezezagun bat errepidera atera ni harrapatu eta bortxatzeko. leku ustez segurutik noalako, eta ilun badago, argiturik dauden bideetatik. baina ezin dut ekidin: segidan eta nahigabe jartzen dut arreta hotsetan; zerbait sumatzen badut atzera begiratzen dut etengabe; eta urrutian gizonezko bat ikusten badut zentzumen guziak jartzen zaizkit adi.

horregatik segitzen dut bakarrik korrika egiten; zerbait gertatzekotan agian ezinen dudalako ekidin, baina nahiago baitut beldurrez korrika egin beldurragatik laster egiteari itzi baino.
📍maddi ane txoperena

text:
how are your child's boundary skills?  the last thing you want is a #teen who can be pushed into doing unhealthy and illegal things. ⠀
⠀
that’s why i’ve put together an online course: the #boundaries and #consent bootcamp, a course for anyone ages 10 and up.  let's set you up as your child's #1 ally, their source of information, their trainer and advisor. ⠀
⠀
sign up for the course yourself and/or share it with your kids.  in the age of #metoo, learning these boundaries and consent skills is essential!⠀
⠀
click my profile link to learn more.

step 4 of our #16stepprogram - on how boys and men can step up and take action for #metoo.

talk to your sons, brothers, nephews and younger friends

cis-hetero men and their relationships with other men and boys are often infected with a lack of emotional openness. this is your time to start talking to your sons, your younger brothers, nephews, friends, cousins and colleagues. take the lead with having difficult conversations around gender discrimination, sexual assault, coercion, consent, masculinities, and sexualities and link it back to personal experiences and behaviours. understand that you control your own circle of influence and that you can create an impact on younger or more impressionable men and boys around you.

text:
so, my #lsat is saturday. someone asked me yesterday what if i fail. what if i'm not good enough.  my first thought was, don't you think i already had that thought? but, also to whom would i be failing? you?  a few years ago i lost everything and started over with a #tbi no #selfworth a child with sever #trauma and more violence than most people make it through.  i became my own #lawyer, my own advocate. i lost friends and family and you know what i did, succeeded.... #survival in domestic violence is hard enough (75%of domestic homicides happen after the victim leaves) but #succeeding is a whole other level. i rebuilt my life while walking into 400mph winds blew shit and more shit at me. 
so you see, failure is subjective, will i be disappointed if i don't make it. damn right but will i retreat and hide. hell no!! i can still do a lot of good! 
if you know someone who needs help #man and #woman. don't blame them or ask them why don't they leave, you don't know what happens behind closed doors. #gunviolence #rape #torture #threats #stalking #desruction. 
this is why i am becoming a #lawyer 
#prelaw #lawschool #brainsandbeauty #deeper #sucess #domesticviolence #plussizemodel #lovemyself #plans #hustle #lifeasabruin @wca3801 @heartlandfam @bellevueuniversity #metoo #freedom #lovethysef #education
name: Sassy Functional Dysfunction

name: The Word for This
pre_proc_tweet:
the process between me and the brave survivors who share here is different every time. sometimes it’s a quick back and foh; others become conversations that last long after i’ve published their story. sometimes i preserve their words exactly as written; others seek more active editing or creative transformation. this time, as i began to read, i could feel the cadence of the cycle of self-blame, of questioning, of abject fear, of determination, over and over again. i heard that inner voice, caught the tone shift from narration to something more internal. so we decided to make that pa of the story. and i want her to know: i see you, i hear you, and i believe you. read her story at the link in my profile, then drop a comment below and let her know you’re with her, too.
✒🖤

text:
desde que mi cuerpo empezó a cambiar, desde que mis senos empezaron a crecer, no podía salir a la calle sin que algún hombre me gritara algo denigrante. a mí, una niña de 12 años en ese tiempo. en ese momento trataba de no darle importancia y creía que no me afectaba, en realidad sí me afectó enormemente. caminaba con la espalda curveada intentando esconder mis senos, no me vestía con ropa que me gustaba por miedo a que me gritaran cosas o peor que alguien intentara violarme en la calle. siempre me comporté de una forma tratando de no llamar la atención de ningún hombre y correr menos riesgo de sufrir cualquier abuso. estás son tan solo una de las pocas formas en que me afectó el acoso callejero. sin contar mi baja autoestima y de como me sentía un objeto sexual. en mi cabeza yo no era una persona, yo era un par de tetas que caminaban y los hombres no miraban más allá. es difícil crecer de esta forma, no puedo imaginar lo que viven las víctimas de abusos sexuales. el acoso callejero juega con tu salud mental, creces preguntándote si sos una persona que tiene valor. no es normal, no normalicemos el acoso callejero. pd. gracias por leerme 🙏🏼
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

•entertainment✨(celebrity): singing artist chris brown has sued 24 year old french model for accusing him of rape and abuse. police struggled with the details given by the model for how the event took place. tmz has reported that “one source directly connected to the case tells us, ‘the weakest part of the case is the alleged victim’s statement to police.’” it is claimed that the alleged assault was committed by brown’s bodyguard, an associate of brown, and brown himself. it was also claimed that there were a dozen of other people in the room that the event took place and cellphones were confiscated by his bodyguard. brown has denied all accusations through a statement (that has been deleted) “i wanna make it perfectly clear...... this is false and a whole lot of cap! (sic) nnnnnnnneeeeeeeeeevvvvvvvvvveeeeeerrrrrr!!!!!! for my daughter and my family this is so disprespectful and is against my character and morals!!!!!" police released the three (brown, friend, and bodyguard) tuesday after being questioned 24 hours previously. brown has received support from other celebrities such as justin bieber, nick cannon, and t.i. who all “stand behind him”. they show their belief in brown and “know him” for who he is.

text:
grief... it sweeps like a tidal wave when you least expect it. and when the waves crash, you have to press in....allow it to take you under. i have found if grief is not felt, it paralyzes your being - it holds you captive until it is allowed to breathe.
grief looks like long breaths. it looks like hot tears. it looks like pages upon pages of written words, shaking the pen in your hand. grief looks like anger - furious rage. and sometimes, grief looks like an old friend sitting on your porch with a glass of lemonade.
grief takes many forms....for me, the waves of grief come at random. grief over abuse, broken promises, lost trust and buried dreams. grief over places i once belonged and people i once trusted. grief over religion that once held me and chains i once thought were good. grief over the loss of innocence and the bravery of saying, "not only me....but us too". my story sometimes feels "other than".... like this surely must have happened to someone "other" than me....other than us. and yet, when the waves hit, it becomes all too real.
but, just like the burial of a seed underground, life breaks forth from the dark. joy fills the air with sunlight and new birth. hope raises its hand and says, "it ain't over yet" 
yes, there is pain in so many of our stories. and yet, there is beauty and new beginnings. grief and joy are so delicately woven together... like sisters with different birthdays. so much of each comes from the same place... and yet, so much is deeply different. 
today, my sister is grief. and today, my sister is also joy. both are welcome at my table. both have earned a place in my home. and, as i dance with grief, i also dance with joy.
.
.

text:
🌺 when women with passion and purpose come together, it’s like entering into another dimension.
✨
the energy is so palpable you can almost reach out and touch it. the creativity is off the charts inspiring and the bonds formed are not fleeting encounters, but deep soul connections.
✨
it is a space so supportive and nurturing that you can experience a sense of true belonging. space where you can be comfortable, and unapologetically authentic and where your true essence and unique gifts are celebrated.
✨
this is how we network soul sister circle style; with heart, with intention and with a whole lot of soul.
🌺
the aim of #redtentaustralia is to connect, collaborate and create a #community of strong and educated women in a #supportive & nurturing environment. our direction is governed by the need to nurture a symbiotic relationship with the earth. we believe everyone is connected. we believe that the earth needs us to remember our ancestral knowledge & go back to "the old ways."
✨
it is our goal to connect women with their natural wisdom in all areas of their lives, to initiate and increase their #healing.
✨
it’s our hope for everyone who enters each red tent to experience a sense of belonging, sisterhood and strength that stays with them from then on.
✨
red tent australia is a national, non-profit, social enterprise supporting women and encouraging them to start their own red tent in their own community
✨
our regular #retreats offer #yoga #meditation #palm readings #reflexology #tarot #aromatherapy facials #remedial massage #sound chime relaxation #reiki #bonfire #dancing. ✨
our next retreat is on saturday 25th – sunday 26th may 2019 :: you are warmly welcome to join us. tickets will sell out, see link for more info or to book, in our profile bio.
🌺
#womensretreats  #healingretreats #invokingthewarriorwoman2019 #boundlessselfloveretreat #acceptance #belonging #community #womenscircles #bslr2019 #redtentau  #metoo  #goddess  #support

text: very proud to be sharing this work created in collaboration with @micaela_mamede for her awe inspiring choreography performance at gibney dance, this is #maria2018. produced and performed by an ensemble of non-us immigrant women and allies, maria tells the all too common story of violence and silence immigrant women face. this whole project was made possible by micaela and her unwavering visual mission to share her own voice. she's since gained the support of the #healmetoo festival, a grassroots foundation working to heal victims of sexual violence by funding creative, therapeutic outlets for victims. please join us at the first ever nyc heal me too festival march 27-april 19, 2019. to learn more about their work, please follow @micaela_mamede and @healmetoofest and visit www.healmetoofest.com #metoo #womenshistorymonth #intimatepartnerviolence #healing - makeup by @batamakeup and cast: #danutapetrow-sek #emilyteller #hayetmoutfi, #krishnawashburn #malaikacambridge #maluavalos #mariasek #micaelamamede and #pearlbhatnagar - thank you ladies. xo

text:
#하하민주 #하루에하나민감한주제 #4 #혐오
...
2018년도 대한민국 전체를 강타한 큰 키워드가 몇가지 있다. 상반기에 큰 이슈가 되었던 #metoo 운동을 그 대표주자로 삼을것이다. 사실 미투운동은 여성권익 증진을 위해 필요한 것이었다. 하지만 전체적인 큰 흐름이 그들의 불합리와 차별받고있었던 억울함과 분노로 인해 점점 우월주의의 성향을 띄게 된 것은 사실이다. 하지만 이러한 문제들은 오늘의 포스팅에서 다룰 내용이 아니다. 오늘의 주제는 "혐오"이다.

혐오의 사전적 정의는 '어떠한 것을 증오, 불결함 등의 이유로 싫어하거나 기피하는 감정으로, 불쾌,기피함,싫어함 등의 감정이 복합적으로 이루어진 비교적 강한 감정을 의미' 한다고 정의 되어있다.
사전적 정의를 보다가 흥미로운 것을 발견했는데, 네이버에 있는 교회용어사전의 정의를 찾게 되었다. '싫어하고 아주 미워함. 원어적으로 '역겹고 구역질 날 정도로 미워하다'는 뜻으로, 하나님께서 미워하시는 우상에 대하여 자주 쓰인다' 라고 기술되어있는 것에서 내가 하고싶은 말을 찾을 수 있었다.

일단, 혐오의 대상은 사람이 되면 안된다. 정의에서 볼 수 있듯이, 소위 말하는 증오, 불결함, 기피함 등의 감정들은 하나님이 만드신 피조물에겐 어울릴 수 없는 단어이다.

교회용어사전에 기술된 혐오는 하나님이 우상들을 미워하시고 증오하실때 쓰이는 표현이다. 하나님의 혐오는 우리와 하나님 사이를 끊어놓는 모든 것들을 향한 광범위한 분노이다. 
사회적 차원의 문제를 보던 시야를 조금 좁혀서 현재 나의 생활범위 안으로 시야를 좁혀보자. 스스로를 크리스천이라고 생각하고 스스로를 예수님을 닮아가길 원하는 제자라고 생각했던 우리에게 혐오라는 단어는 어떤 의미인가? 우상들을 향한 하나님의 분노를 우리는 가지고있는가? 하나님의 증오를 우리는 가지고있는가? "3 너는 나 외에는 다른 신들을 네게 두지 말라 4 너를 위하여 새긴 우상을 만들지 말고 또 위로 하늘에 있는 것이나 아래로 땅에 있는 것이나 땅 아래 물 속에 있는 것의 어떤 형상도 만들지 말며 5 그것들에게 절하지 말며 그것들을 섬기지 말라 나 네 하나님 여호와는 질투하는 하나님인즉 나를 미워하는 자의 죄를 갚되 아버지로부터 아들에게로 삼사 대까지 이르게 하거니와 (출 20 : 3~5)" 출애굽 직후 하나님께서 이스라엘 백성에게 하셨던 십계명의 첫번째는 "하나님만을 예배하라", 두번째는 "우상을 만들어 섬기지 말라"이다. 여기서 질투하시는 하나님의 의미는 단순히 우상들을 미워해서 그런 것이 아니라 하나님이 우리를 사랑하시고, 우리도 하나님을 사랑하길 원하시기에 말씀하시는 것이다. "네 하나님 여호와는 소멸하는 불이시요 질투하시는 하나님이시니라 (신 4 : 24)" 출애급 당시에 하신 이 말씀은 오늘날 우리가 살아가는 이 시대에도 여전히 적용된다. 하나님은 언제나 우리를 사랑하신다. 그리고 우리가 하나님보다 더 사랑하고있는 무엇인가를 끊임 없이 증오하시고 혐오하신다. 그리고 "조각한 신상을 섬기며 허무한 것으로 자랑하는 자는 다 수치를 당할 것이라 너희 신들아 여호와께 경배할지어다(시 97 : 7)" 라고 말씀하신다. 이제 우리가 할 수 있는 선택은 두가지밖엔 없다. 하나님의 사랑을 뒷전으로 한 채 여전히 우리가 사랑하고 있던 것들에 집중할것인지, 그 모든 것을 뒤로하고 언제까지나 사랑하시는 그 하나님의 사랑에 돌아갈 것인지 선택해야 할 것이다. "나를 사랑하고 내 계명을 지키는 자에게는 천 대까지 은혜를 베푸느니라(출 20 : 6) "

stop_filter_tweet: 오 ... 2018년도 대한민국 전체를 강타한 큰 키워드가 몇가지 있다 . 상반기에 큰 이슈가 되었던 운동을 그 대표주자로 삼을것이다 . 사실 미투운동은 여성권익 증진을 위해 필요한 것이었다 . 하지만 전체적인 큰 흐름이 그들의 불합리와 차별받고있었던 억울함과 분노로 인해 점점 우월주의의 성향을 띄게 된 것은 사실이다 . 하지만 이러한 문제들은 오늘의 포스팅에서 다룰 내용이 아니다 . 오늘의 주제는 `` 혐오 '' 이다 . 혐오의 사전적 정의는 '어떠한 것을 증오 , 불결함 등의 이유로 싫어하거나 기피하는 감정으로 , 불쾌 , 기피함 , 싫어함 등의 감정이 복합적으로 이루어진 비교적 강한 감정을 의미 ' 한다고 정의 되어있다 . 사전적 정의를 보다가 흥미로운 것을 발견했는데 , 네이버에 있는 교회용어사전의 정의를 찾게 되었다 . '싫어하고 아주 미워함 . 원어적으로 '역겹고 구역질 날 정도로 미워하다'는 뜻으로 , 하나님께서 미워하시는 우상에 대하여 자주 쓰인다 ' 라고 기술되어있는 것에서 내가 하고싶은 말을 찾을 수 있었다 . 일단 , 혐오의 대상은 사람이 되면 안된다 . 정의에서 볼 수 있듯이 , 소위 말하는 증오 , 불결함 , 기피함 등의 감정들은 하나님이 만드신 피조물에겐 어울릴 수 없는 단어이다 . 교회용어사전에 기술된 혐오는 하나님이 우상들을 미워하시고 증오하실때 쓰이는 표현이다 . 하나님의 혐오는 우리와 하나님 사이를 끊어놓는 모든 것들을 향한 광범위한 분노이다 . 사회적 차원의 문제를 보던 시야를 조금 좁혀서 현재 나의 생활범위 안으로 시야를 좁혀보자 . 스스로를 크리스천이라고 생각하고 스스로를 예수님을 닮아가길 원하는 제자라고 생각했던 우리에게 혐오라는 단어는 어떤 의미인가 ? 우상들을 향한 하나님의 분노를 우리는 가지고있는가 ? 하나님의 증오를 우리는 가지고있는가 ? `` 3 너는 나 외에는 다른 신들을 네게 두지 말라 4 너를 위하여 새긴 우상을 만들지 말고 또 위로 하늘에 있는 것이나 아래로 땅에 있는 것이나 땅 아래 물 속에 있는 것의 어떤 형상도 만들지 말며 5 그것들에게 절하지 말며 그것들을 섬기지 말라 나 네 하나님 여호와는 질투하는 하나님인즉 나를 미워하는 자의 죄를 갚되 아버지로부터 아들에게로 삼사 대까지 이르게 하거니와 ( 출 20 : 3~5 ) '' 출애굽 직후 하나님께서 이스라엘 백성에게 하셨던 십계명의 첫번째는 `` 하나님만을 예배하라 '' , 두번째는 `` 우상을 만들어 섬기지 말라 '' 이다 . 여기서 질투하시는 하나님의 의미는 단순히 우상들을 미워해서 그런 것이 아니라 하나님이 우리를 사랑하시고 , 우리도 하나님을 사랑하길 원하시기에 말씀하시는 것이다 . `` 네 하나님 여호와는 소멸하는 불이시요 질투하시는 하나님이시니라 ( 신 4 : 24 ) '' 출애급 당시에 하신 이 말씀은 오늘날 우리가 살아가는 이 시대에도 여전히 적용된다 . 하나님은 언제나 우리를 사랑하신다 . 그리고 우리가 하나님보다 더 사랑하고있는 무엇인가를 끊임 없이 증오하시고 혐오하신다 . 그리고 `` 조각한 신상을 섬기며 허무한 것으로 자랑하는 자는 다 수치를 당할 것이라 너희 신들아 여호와께 경배할지어다 ( 시 97 : 7 ) '' 라고 말씀하신다 . 이제 우리가 할 수 있는 선택은 두가지밖엔 없다 . 하나님의 사랑을 뒷전으로 한 채 여전히 우리가 사랑하고 있던 것들에 집중할것인지 , 그 모든 것을 뒤로하고 언제까지나 사랑하시는 그 하나님의 사랑에 돌아갈 것인지 선택해야 할 것이다 . `` 나를 사랑하고 내 계명을 지키는 자에게는 천 대까지 은혜를 베푸느니라 ( 출 20 : 6 ) ``

text:
so i did a thing today. i took another step towards healing and helping others ❤️ i can't wait to see what god has planned for me next! as scary as speaking up about rape can be, it cannot compare to helping others know they are not alone. please pray for me through this struggle! •
as always, if anyone needs help, feel free to reach out! i am here for you ❤️

text: 2 years ago i marched in dc & it ignited the activist in me. words can not describe what an amazing & transformative experience it was. saturday i returned. this was a decision i wrestled with given all the controversy surrounding the leaders of the march. i in no way condone antisemitism or discrimination against anyone. i marched in dc again for pay equity, ending gender-based violence, birth control & abortion access, dismantling mass incarceration, universal health care for all, equality for all & to show this pres. and administration that we are not going anywhere. i am not going anywhere. while it was very different from the 2017 march i am glad i went. it reminded me why i’ve gotten involved, how its inspired thousands of women to run for office, how much we’ve accomplished in 2 years & how much more there is still to do #resist #persist #womenswave #womensmarch2019 #womensmarch #dc #thisisnotnormal #nastywoman #timesup #enough #metoo #lovefirst #thisiswhatdemocracylookslike #rupaul4president ✊🏻☮️❤️🌈🗽🌊

text:
badgering her until she finally says yes or at least stops saying no isn't respecting her or her choices. once you've got your answer, leave it at that. consent is enthusiastic. don't do the grey stuff. if it's not clear, ask for clarification *without pressuring*. if it is clear and just not the answer you want, deal with it. 
respect the no. respect the hesitation. respect her. 
n.b. this 100% goes for women respecting men's answer as well. *no one* should be pressuring anyone into sex or dating or whatever it is they've said no to. period.

text:
mic test 1,2… 1,2. calling out all cheaters, calling you all out.

hard topic to talk about, and i’ve been wanting to talk about it for years. i’ve had sex with girls who were in relationships, a couple of them were married, the others in long term relationships. i’m trying not to beat around the bush here. i don’t want to muddle the word “sex” with “sexual advances” as god knows i’ve made plenty of those over my time (hey i’ve had my fair share of girls making aggressive sexual advances at #metoo). with the girls: fact is i knew what i was doing felt wrong but i went there anyways. i talk a lot and ask a lot of questions. i prefer my emotions out rather than in. more than a few times i’ve tried to bring up the deed in conversation but i’m usually faced with 1 of 2 things; 1) i’m made to feel silly for thinking anything of it! are you seriously saying you’re feeling guilty right now?! um, yes? yes i am?! 2) i’m introduced to the concept of “keeping a secret” something i’ve never done and highly doubt i could ever do.

with the guys: i’ve always had closer girl friends than guy friends. i still do. i consider my friends wives to be my mates. it hurts then to see what i’ve seen on overseas trips with the boys. when i confronted the guys about the issue i expressed that i was single, which somewhat gave me the right to do whatever i wanted, but you guys are married, with children! the response? who the fuck are you to judge justin? floored. speechless. i get it.

back to the girls again: i crossed the line once and admitted to one of the girls what her guy was doing. what was the response? shut the fuck up justin i don’t want to hear it!!! back to the guys again: just last year a mate was parading that he got a bare back blow job overseas. congratulations man, you just gave your kids an std.

i’m talking about it because everyone world wide seems to think that encouraging conversation is a great way to begin resolving big issues, but from what i’ve learned from experience; talking is the last thing the guilty want to do.

also on medium: https://medium.com/@justinfox_30083/

text:
every year, january always feels like the longest month of the year, every single year. i got in a car accident, moved, managed to get sick twice 💀 and because of trump, a lot of things are basically just trash... but i digress. 
classes start next week and for those who have seen me last semester, they know that i’ve been working to start a sexual assault awareness campaign called ‘the resistance’ on bowie state’s campus. i’m officially launching the social media accounts next week and you will be seeing more activism around campus. if anyone would love to help out just dm or text me as always. follow the campaign page @resistancecampaign 
happy wednesday everyone 💖 keep being great :)
and also: a special thanks to everyone whose supported thus far, but especially the @bsufollowers @vcdma department and @jtknoxroxs 
#bowiestate #activism #bsu #sexualassaultawareness #resistance #theresistancecampaign #metoo

text:
news from #israel

district psychiatrist dr jacob charnes was cross examined all day on the 24th jan. the case was adjourned to the 13th and 26th of march. 
according to leifer's lawyers, the district psychiatrist advised the court that the previous psychiatrists who had found leifer fit for trial had made a 'mistake'. dr charnes recommended that the judge defer leifer's mental fitness to another panel of experts. 
i don't understand how the district psychiatrist, who signed off reports that found leifer fit, could think they were mistaken or recommend another freaking panel of experts! 
hasn't this case had enough 'expert' panels???
sometimes it feels like this will never end!
-
-
malka leifer, my former school principal is under custody in israel but is claiming mental illness in order to avoid extradition. 
meanwhile in australia she has 74 charges of sexual assault to face and numerous victims waiting for a chance to face her in court. 
for more information on my campaign for justice visit my facebook page - dassi erlich; beyond a survivor

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian
